{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_H63mlGYYgoMwhhUibb6NNzzQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→Ticket: TST-001\n     3→Slug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n     4→Status: READY\n     5→Updated: 2026-03-18\n     6→Owner: backend-lead, frontend-lead\n     7→PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\n     8→Plan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\n     9→Research: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n    10→Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\n    11→Reports:\n    12→  tests: aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n    13→  review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n    14→  reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n    15→  qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n    16→---\n    17→\n    18→# Tasklist: TST-001 — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n    19→\n    20→> Единственный источник правды для implement/review/qa.\n    21→> Всегда начинайте чтение с `## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:SPEC_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`, затем `## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL`, затем `## AIDD:NEXT_3`.\n    22→\n    23→## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n    24→Updated: 2026-03-18\n    25→Ticket: TST-001\n    26→Stage: tasklist\n    27→Status: READY\n    28→\n    29→### TL;DR\n    30→- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement for mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and SSE-based frontend role sync\n    31→- Current focus (1 checkbox): I1 - Database migration + RBAC domain model\n    32→- Done since last pack: PRD finalized, Plan created with 5 phases, research findings integrated\n    33→- Risk level: medium — SSE infrastructure exists but profile service integration needs verification\n    34→\n    35→### Scope & boundaries\n    36→- Allowed paths (patch boundaries):\n    37→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/` (new package)\n    38→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/` (migrations)\n    39→  - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n    40→  - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n    41→  - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n    42→  - `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n    43→- Forbidden / out-of-scope:\n    44→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/` — no changes to note domain\n    45→  - `frontend/src/pages/notes/` — no changes to note UI\n    46→  - Spring Security integration — using custom WebFlux filters\n    47→  - WebSocket — using existing SSE infrastructure instead\n    48→- Integrations / dependencies:\n    49→  - Profile service API — fetch roles by namespace:reference (fallback to local DB if unavailable)\n    50→  - PostgreSQL — rbac_audit_log table\n    51→  - Caffeine cache — role caching with 5min TTL\n    52→  - SSE endpoint — extends existing flow events infrastructure\n    53→\n    54→### Decisions & defaults (living)\n    55→- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false), `rbac.audit-only` (default: true for Phase 1)\n    56→- Contract/API: X-Profile-Key header format `namespace:reference`, X-Profile-Auth for verification\n    57→- Data model changes: New `rbac_audit_log` table with JSONB metadata\n    58→- Observability: Micrometer timer on RBAC filter, Caffeine cache stats, SSE connection metrics\n    59→\n    60→### Test policy (iteration budget)\n    61→- Cadence: checkpoint\n    62→- Profile: targeted\n    63→- Tasks:\n    64→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`\n    65→  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n    66→- Filters:\n    67→  - `RbacWebFilterTest`\n    68→  - `ProfileRoleServiceTest`\n    69→  - `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n    70→- Budget minutes: 10\n    71→- Known flaky / failing: none\n    72→\n    73→### Commands quickstart (copy/paste)\n    74→- Format: cmd\n    75→- Tests (manual):\n    76→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*Rbac*\"`\n    77→  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n    78→- Run/Dev:\n    79→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:bootRun`\n    80→  - `npm run dev` (frontend)\n    81→- DB migration: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n    82→\n    83→### Open questions / blockers\n    84→- None — all questions resolved via PRD decisions Q1-Q5\n    85→\n    86→### Blockers summary (handoff)\n    87→- None\n    88→\n    89→### References\n    90→- Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (OUTDATED — uses WebSocket, follow Plan for SSE)\n    91→- PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md (Status: READY)\n    92→- Research: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n    93→- Plan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md (Status: READY, source of truth for implementation)\n    94→\n    95→---\n    96→\n    97→## AIDD:SPEC_PACK\n    98→Updated: 2026-03-18\n    99→Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (status: draft — OUTDATED)\n   100→\n   101→- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement on mutation APIs with auditable role operations and SSE-based frontend synchronization\n   102→- Non-goals:\n   103→  - UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n   104→  - Migration of historical access logs\n   105→  - Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n   106→  - WebSocket (Spec says WebSocket, but Plan uses SSE — follow Plan)\n   107→- Key decisions:\n   108→  - Backend: Custom WebFlux filter for RBAC (no Spring Security)\n   109→  - Auth: X-Profile-Key header-based identity extraction\n   110→  - Frontend: React + Zustand (not Redux as in Spec)\n   111→  - Session Sync: SSE (Server-Sent Events) — NOT WebSocket, NOT Polling\n   112→  - Cache: Caffeine with 5min TTL\n   113→  - Audit: PostgreSQL table `rbac_audit_log` with JSONB metadata\n   114→- Risks:\n   115→  - R-001: Profile service unavailable → Circuit breaker, fail-closed, cache roles\n   116→  - R-002: Cache stale roles after assignment → Cache invalidation on role change\n   117→  - R-003: SSE connection memory leak → Proper cleanup on disconnect\n   118→  - R-004: Audit log write failures → Async logging, error queue\n   119→  - R-005: RBAC filter performance degradation → Caffeine cache, async audit\n   120→  - R-006: Breaking change to existing APIs → Feature flags, audit-only mode first\n   121→  - R-007: Component scan misses RBAC beans → Add to all profile configs\n   122→  - R-008: Missing profile service integration → Define contract or implement local role storage\n   123→\n   124→## AIDD:TEST_STRATEGY\n   125→- Unit:\n   126→  - Scope: RBAC middleware logic, role caching, audit log formatting, useRoleGuard hook\n   127→  - Files: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `AuditLogServiceTest`, `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n   128→- Integration:\n   129→  - Scope: RBAC filter + profile service client, audit log DB writes, SSE endpoint connection handling\n   130→  - Files: `RbacIntegrationTest`, `RoleEventsControllerTest`\n   131→- Contract:\n   132→  - Scope: API response schemas (403 format), SSE event format\n   133→  - Files: Contract tests for `/api/profiles/role-events` endpoint\n   134→- E2E/Stand:\n   135→  - Critical paths:\n   136→    - flow.admin-change-role: Admin assigns role → user receives SSE update\n   137→    - flow.unauthorized-access: User attempts restricted action → 403 + audit log\n   138→    - flow.live-session-update: Role change propagates to frontend within 5 seconds\n   139→- Test data:\n   140→  - Fixtures: Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions, regular user with limited role, user with missing headers\n   141→\n   142→---\n   143→\n   144→## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION\n   145→> Конкретные команды/фильтры запуска (execution‑уровень).\n   146→- profile: targeted\n   147→- tasks:\n   148→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`\n   149→  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n   150→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacIntegrationTest*\"`\n   151→- filters:\n   152→  - `RbacWebFilterTest` — filter logic tests\n   153→  - `ProfileRoleServiceTest` — caching and role resolution tests\n   154→  - `AuditLogServiceTest` — audit logging tests\n   155→  - `useRoleGuard.test.ts` — frontend hook tests\n   156→- when: checkpoint\n   157→- reason: Fast feedback on RBAC module changes; full suite on PR\n   158→\n   159→---\n   160→\n   161→## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL\n   162→> Полный список итераций реализации (от 1 до N). Должен быть **детальнее плана** и не оставлять пробелов.\n   163→> Канонический формат итерации: `- [ ] I{N}: <title> (iteration_id: I{N})`\n   164→\n   165→- [x] I1: Database migration + RBAC domain model (iteration_id: I1) (link: commit-a1f45f2)\n   166→  - parent_iteration_id: none\n   167→  - Goal: Create database schema for audit logging and establish RBAC domain model\n   168→  - Outputs:\n   169→    - `db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` — migration for rbac_audit_log table\n   170→    - `Role.java` — Role enum (ADMIN, USER, VIEWER)\n   171→    - `ProfileIdentity.java` — Value object for namespace:reference\n   172→    - `Permission.java` — Permission enum (READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN)\n   173→    - `RbacDecision.java` — Decision record\n   174→    - `AuditLogEntity.java` — JPA entity for audit log\n   175→    - `AuditLogRepository.java` — Spring Data repository\n   176→  - DoD: Migration runs successfully, all domain classes compile with tests, repository can save/retrieve entries\n   177→  - Boundaries:\n   178→    - Only database and domain layer — no services or filters yet\n   179→    - Do not modify existing tables\n   180→  - Priority: high\n   181→  - Blocking: true\n   182→  - deps: []\n   183→  - locks: []\n   184→  - Expected paths:\n   185→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/`\n   186→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/`\n   187→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/`\n   188→  - Size budget:\n   189→    - max_files: 10\n   190→    - max_loc: 500\n   191→  - Commands:\n   192→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n   193→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLog*\"`\n   194→  - Exit criteria:\n   195→    - Migration applies without errors\n   196→    - Unit tests pass for domain classes\n   197→    - Repository integration test passes\n   198→  - Steps:\n   199→    - Create Liquibase changelog for rbac_audit_log table with indexes\n   200→    - Create Role enum with standard roles\n   201→    - Create ProfileIdentity value object with validation\n   202→    - Create Permission enum\n   203→    - Create RbacDecision record\n   204→    - Create AuditLogEntity JPA entity\n   205→    - Create AuditLogRepository interface\n   206→    - Write unit tests for domain classes\n   207→    - Write repository integration test\n   208→  - Tests:\n   209→    - profile: targeted\n   210→    - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLog*\" --tests \"*Role*\"`\n   211→    - filters: `AuditLogRepositoryTest`, `RoleTest`\n   212→  - Acceptance mapping: AC-2 (audit log structure)\n   213→  - Risks & mitigations:\n   214→    - Migration conflicts with existing schema → Use separate rbac changelog file\n   215→    - JSONB type not supported → Verify PostgreSQL version compatibility\n   216→  - Dependencies: PostgreSQL database, Liquibase\n   217→\n   218→- [ ] I2: RBAC WebFilter + Audit logging service (iteration_id: I2)\n   219→  - parent_iteration_id: I1\n   220→  - Goal: Implement RBAC WebFlux filter for mutation API protection and async audit logging\n   221→  - Outputs:\n   222→    - `RbacWebFilter.java` — Main RBAC filter (Order: HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100)\n   223→    - `AuditLogService.java` — Async audit logging service\n   224→    - `RbacPathMatcher.java` — Path matching logic for protected routes\n   225→    - `RbacProperties.java` — Configuration properties\n   226→    - `RbacConfiguration.java` — Spring configuration\n   227→  - DoD: Filter intercepts POST/PUT/DELETE, returns 403 for unauthorized, audit log entries written, config loaded\n   228→  - Boundaries:\n   229→    - No profile service integration yet — use mock/stub\n   230→    - No caching yet\n   231→    - Do not modify existing controllers\n   232→  - Priority: high\n   233→  - Blocking: true\n   234→  - deps: [I1]\n   235→  - locks: []\n   236→  - Expected paths:\n   237→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/`\n   238→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/`\n   239→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/`\n   240→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/`\n   241→  - Size budget:\n   242→    - max_files: 8\n   243→    - max_loc: 800\n   244→  - Commands:\n   245→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacWebFilterTest*\"`\n   246→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLogServiceTest*\"`\n   247→  - Exit criteria:\n   248→    - Filter unit tests pass with mocked role service\n   249→    - Audit log service writes entries asynchronously\n   250→    - 403 responses returned for unauthorized mutation requests\n   251→    - Configuration properties load correctly\n   252→  - Steps:\n   253→    - Create RbacProperties configuration record\n   254→    - Create RbacConfiguration Spring config\n   255→    - Create RbacPathMatcher for protected path patterns\n   256→    - Create AuditLogService with async executor\n   257→    - Create RbacWebFilter with identity extraction\n   258→    - Implement 403 response for denied access\n   259→    - Write unit tests for filter with mocked dependencies\n   260→    - Write integration test for audit logging\n   261→  - Tests:\n   262→    - profile: targeted\n   263→    - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacWebFilter*\" --tests \"*AuditLogService*\"`\n   264→    - filters: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `AuditLogServiceTest`\n   265→  - Acceptance mapping: AC-1 (403 responses), AC-2 (audit logging)\n   266→  - Risks & mitigations:\n   267→    - Filter ordering conflicts → Use Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100\n   268→    - Async audit log failures → Error handling in executor\n   269→  - Dependencies: I1\n   270→\n   271→- [ ] I3: Profile service integration + Role caching (iteration_id: I3)\n   272→  - parent_iteration_id: I2\n   273→  - Goal: Connect to profile service for role resolution with Caffeine caching\n   274→  - Outputs:\n   275→    - `ProfileClient.java` — WebClient for profile service\n   276→    - `ProfileResponse.java` — Profile DTO\n   277→    - `ProfileRoleService.java` — Role resolution with caching\n   278→    - `RbacConfig.java` — Component scan configuration\n   279→  - DoD: Profile client fetches roles, Caffeine cache with 5min TTL, cache invalidation works, fail-closed on errors\n   280→  - Boundaries:\n   281→    - No SSE events yet\n   282→    - Profile service URL configurable\n   283→  - Priority: high\n   284→  - Blocking: true\n   285→  - deps: [I2]\n   286→  - locks: []\n   287→  - Expected paths:\n   288→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/`\n   289→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/`\n   290→  - Size budget:\n   291→    - max_files: 6\n   292→    - max_loc: 400\n   293→  - Commands:\n   294→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileRoleServiceTest*\"`\n   295→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileClientTest*\"`\n   296→  - Exit criteria:\n   297→    - Profile client successfully fetches roles\n   298→    - Cache hit rate > 90% under load\n   299→    - P95 latency < 10ms with cache\n   300→    - Graceful fallback when service unavailable\n   301→  - Steps:\n   302→    - Create ProfileResponse DTO\n   303→    - Create ProfileClient with WebClient\n   304→    - Create ProfileRoleService with Caffeine cache\n   305→    - Implement cache invalidation method\n   306→    - Create RbacConfig for component scanning\n   307→    - Write unit tests for caching behavior\n   308→    - Write integration tests for profile client\n   309→    - Add cache metrics exposure\n   310→  - Tests:\n   311→    - profile: targeted\n   312→    - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileRoleService*\" --tests \"*ProfileClient*\"`\n   313→    - filters: `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `ProfileClientTest`\n   314→  - Acceptance mapping: AC-4 (P95 ≤ 10ms)\n   315→  - Risks & mitigations:\n   316→    - Profile service unavailable → Fail-closed with empty roles\n   317→    - Cache stale data → TTL 5min + explicit invalidation\n   318→  - Dependencies: I2\n   319→\n   320→- [ ] I4: Frontend SSE integration + useRoleGuard hook (iteration_id: I4)\n   321→  - parent_iteration_id: I3\n   322→  - Goal: Implement frontend role synchronization via SSE and role guard hook\n   323→  - Outputs:\n   324→    - `useRoleGuard.ts` — React hook for role checking with SSE\n   325→    - `RoleGuard.tsx` — Component for conditional rendering by role\n   326→    - Updated `profileStore.ts` — SSE subscription and roleVersion\n   327→  - DoD:\n   328→    - useRoleGuard subscribes to SSE on mount\n   329→    - Zustand store updates on role-change events\n   330→    - RoleGuard component conditionally renders children\n   331→    - AdminRoles page uses useRoleGuard hook\n   332→  - Boundaries:\n   333→    - No backend SSE endpoint yet — mock for testing\n   334→    - Minimal changes to existing components\n   335→  - Priority: high\n   336→  - Blocking: true\n   337→  - deps: [I3]\n   338→  - locks: []\n   339→  - Expected paths:\n   340→    - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts`\n   341→    - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx`\n   342→    - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n   343→  - Size budget:\n   344→    - max_files: 4\n   345→    - max_loc: 300\n   346→  - Commands:\n   347→    - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n   348→    - `npm test -- RoleGuard`\n   349→  - Exit criteria:\n   350→    - Hook tests pass\n   351→    - Component renders correctly with/without role\n   352→    - Store updates trigger re-renders\n   353→    - Refactored AdminRoles works as before\n   354→  - Steps:\n   355→    - Add roleVersion and SSE subscription to profileStore\n   356→    - Create useRoleGuard hook with memoized checks\n   357→    - Create RoleGuard component with fallback support\n   358→    - Refactor AdminRoles to use useRoleGuard\n   359→    - Write tests for useRoleGuard hook\n   360→    - Write tests for RoleGuard component\n   361→  - Tests:\n   362→    - profile: targeted\n   363→    - tasks: `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n   364→    - filters: `useRoleGuard.test.ts`, `RoleGuard.test.tsx`\n   365→  - Acceptance mapping: AC-3 (5s sync)\n   366→  - Risks & mitigations:\n   367→    - SSE connection errors → Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff\n   368→    - Memory leaks on unmount → Proper cleanup in useEffect\n   369→  - Dependencies: I3\n   370→\n   371→- [ ] I5: SSE endpoint + Role events (iteration_id: I5)\n   372→  - parent_iteration_id: I4\n   373→  - Goal: Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications and role assignment service\n   374→  - Outputs:\n   375→    - `RoleEventService.java` — SSE event management with Sinks\n   376→    - `RoleEventsController.java` — SSE endpoint controller\n   377→    - `RoleAssignmentService.java` — Role assignment with notifications\n   378→  - DoD:\n   379→    - SSE endpoint at `/api/profiles/role-events`\n   380→    - Role change events broadcast to subscribers\n   381→    - RoleAssignmentService notifies on GRANT/REVOKE\n   382→    - Heartbeat every 30 seconds\n   383→  - Boundaries:\n   384→    - No authentication on SSE endpoint yet (public for now)\n   385→    - In-memory subscription map (no Redis)\n   386→  - Priority: medium\n   387→  - Blocking: false\n   388→  - deps: [I4]\n   389→  - locks: []\n   390→  - Expected paths:\n   391→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/`\n   392→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/`\n   393→  - Size budget:\n   394→    - max_files: 5\n   395→    - max_loc: 400\n   396→  - Commands:\n   397→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RoleEventsController*\"`\n   398→    - `./gradlew :backend-m