{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_2M7QYF95VsZR3BaimwVrAXDE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# PRD — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n     2→\n     3→Status: READY\n     4→Ticket: TST-001\n     5→Updated: 2026-03-18\n     6→\n     7→## Диалог analyst\n     8→\n     9→Ссылка на исследование: `aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n    10→\n    11→\n    12→Вопрос 1 (Blocker): Какие конкретные API/эндпоинты считаются \"критическими\" для RBAC-контроля?\n    13→Зачем: Определяет scope работы и какие middleware/декораторы нужно реализовать\n    14→Варианты: A) Только админские эндпоинты (/admin/*) B) Все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE) C) Список из N конкретных эндпоинтов D) Все API с уровнем доступа > public\n    15→Default: B) Все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n    16→**Ответ: B** — Все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE) требуют RBAC-контроля\n    17→\n    18→Вопрос 2 (Clarification): Какая текущая реализация RBAC используется (библиотека или кастомное решение)?\n    19→Зачем: Определяет архитектуру интеграции live enforcement — расширяем существующее или создаём новое\n    20→Варианты: A) Casbin/OPA/другая библиотека B) Кастомная middleware на JWT-claims C) Ролевая проверка в каждом хендлере вручную D) RBAC отсутствует, нужно с нуля\n    21→Default: B) Кастомная middleware на JWT-claims\n    22→**Ответ: C** — X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n    23→\n    24→Вопрос 3 (Clarification): Какой фронтенд-фреймворк и текущий механизм аутентификации используется?\n    25→Зачем: Определяет подход к синхронизации role guards без перезагрузки страницы\n    26→Варианты: A) React + Context/Redux B) Vue + Pinia/Vuex C) Angular + Guards D) Другой (указать)\n    27→Default: A) React + Context/Redux\n    28→**Ответ: B** — React + Zustand (not Redux)\n    29→\n    30→Вопрос 4 (Clarification): Где должны храниться audit-логи ролевых операций?\n    31→Зачем: Влияет на архитектуру логирования, retention policy и интеграции\n    32→Варианты: A) База данных (отдельная таблица) B) Файловая система (JSONL/CSV) C) Внешний сервис (ELK/Splunk/Datadog) D) Гибрид: БД + архив в файл\n    33→Default: A) База данных (отдельная таблица)\n    34→**Ответ: A** — База данных (отдельная таблица)\n    35→\n    36→Вопрос 5 (Clarification): Какой механизм обновления сессии ожидается на фронтенде?\n    37→Зачем: Определяет техническую реализацию live sync между backend и frontend\n    38→Варианты: A) WebSocket (push-обновления) B) Polling (каждые N секунд) C) SSE (Server-Sent Events) D) Только на действиях пользователя (lazy update)\n    39→Default: A) WebSocket (push-обновления)\n    40→**Ответ: B** — Polling (каждые N секунд) — simpler fallback approach\n    41→\n    42→<!-- Добавьте дополнительные «Вопрос N» по мере диалога. Ответы фиксируйте только в секции AIDD:ANSWERS. -->\n    43→\n    44→## AIDD:ANSWERS\n    45→> Единый формат ответов из чата.\n    46→\n    47→AIDD:ANSWERS Q1=B; Q2=C; Q3=B; Q4=A; Q5=B\n    48→\n    49→## AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS\n    50→- **Paths**: `src/middleware:src/auth:src/routes:frontend/src/guards:frontend/src/store:frontend/src/context:src/models:src/db/migrations`\n    51→- **Keywords**: `RBAC,roles,permissions,roleGuard,requireRole,checkPermission,403,audit,session,middleware,JWT,claims,auth,redux,context,websocket,socket,push,notification,grant,revoke,denied,accessControl`\n    52→- **Notes**:\n    53→  1. Найти текущую JWT middleware и как она обрабатывает claims\n    54→  2. Найти существующие role/permission checks в handlers\n    55→  3. Найти frontend auth flow (Redux actions/reducers для auth)\n    56→  4. Найти существующие route guards на frontend\n    57→  5. Проверить polling requirements\n    58→  6. Найти структуру БД для таблиц users, roles, permissions\n    59→  7. Определить формат audit-логов если уже существуют\n    60→\n    61→## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n    62→- FS-RBAC-03 spec requires live RBAC enforcement on critical API endpoints\n    63→- Need to add audit logging for role operations and 403 responses\n    64→- Frontend role guards must sync with session updates without page refresh\n    65→- Ticket: TST-001\n    66→\n    67→## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n    68→- All critical APIs must enforce RBAC with 403 on violations\n    69→- Role operations must be auditable\n    70→- Frontend must reflect role changes without refresh\n    71→\n    72→## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n    73→None\n    74→\n    75→## AIDD:RISKS\n    76→- Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\n    77→- Session desync between backend/frontend → polling mechanism\n    78→- Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\n    79→\n    80→## AIDD:DECISIONS\n    81→- Live RBAC enforcement required per FS-RBAC-03 spec → compliance requirement\n    82→- Frontend sync without refresh → UX requirement for seamless role updates\n    83→- **Q1**: Critical APIs = все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n    84→- **Q2**: Текущая реализация = X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n    85→- **Q3**: Frontend = React + Zustand (not Redux)\n    86→- **Q4**: Audit logs = база данных (отдельная таблица)\n    87→- **Q5**: Session sync = Polling (fallback approach, simpler to implement)\n    88→\n    89→## AIDD:GOALS\n    90→- Enforce live RBAC across critical APIs\n    91→- Add auditable role operations trail\n    92→- Synchronize frontend role guards with live session updates\n    93→\n    94→## AIDD:NON_GOALS\n    95→- UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n    96→- Migration of historical access logs\n    97→- Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n    98→\n    99→## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n   100→- AC-1: Critical APIs return 403 for unauthorized role access\n   101→- AC-2: All role operations are logged with timestamp, user, action\n   102→- AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of session change\n   103→\n   104→## AIDD:METRICS\n   105→- RBAC check latency P95 → ≤ 10ms\n   106→- Frontend role sync delay → ≤ 5 seconds\n   107→- Audit log coverage → 100% of role operations\n   108→\n   109→## AIDD:ROLL_OUT\n   110→- **Phase 1 (MVP)**: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging\n   111→  - Feature flag: `rbac-enforcement-enabled` (default: false)\n   112→  - Rollback: Disable flag to revert to legacy auth\n   113→- **Phase 2**: Polling-based session sync\n   114→  - Feature flag: `session-polling-enabled` (default: false)\n   115→  - Rollback: Disable flag, frontend uses cached session only\n   116→- **Phase 3**: Frontend role guards integration\n   117→  - Feature flag: `live-role-guards` (default: false)\n   118→  - Rollback: Revert to page-refresh session validation\n   119→- **Phase 4**: End-to-end validation\n   120→  - Load testing RBAC latency (target P95 ≤ 10ms)\n   121→  - Monitor audit log storage growth\n   122→  - Verify polling interval doesn't overload backend (target: 30s interval)\n   123→\n   124→## 1. Обзор\n   125→- **Название продукта/фичи**: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n   126→- **Исходные артефакты**: `aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`, `aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`, `aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n   127→- **Дата/версия**: 2026-03-18 v1\n   128→- **Краткое описание**: Реализация live RBAC enforcement для всех мутационных API (POST/PUT/DELETE), добавление аудит-логирования ролевых операций и 403-ответов, синхронизация frontend role guards с backend-сессией через polling (30s interval) без перезагрузки страницы.\n   129→\n   130→## 2. Контекст и проблемы\n   131→- **Текущая ситуация**: Система использует X-Profile-Key header-based auth middleware для RBAC, но live enforcement не реализован для всех критических API. Frontend на React + Zustand не получает live-обновлений при изменении ролей пользователя. Audit-логи ролевых операций отсутствуют.\n   132→- **Проблемы/гипотезы**:\n   133→  1. Нет единой точки контроля RBAC для всех мутационных API — потенциальные security gaps\n   134→  2. Frontend не синхронизируется с изменениями ролей в реальном времени — пользователи видят устаревшие permissions\n   135→  3. Отсутствие audit trail для ролевых операций — невозможно отследить кто и когда получил/потерял доступ\n   136→  4. 403-ответы не логируются — сложно анализировать попытки несанкционированного доступа\n   137→- **Затронутые сегменты**: Все аутентифицированные пользователи системы (100%), администраторы управляющие ролями\n   138→\n   139→## 3. Цели и метрики успеха\n   140→- **North Star / основная метрика**: 100% мутационных API (POST/PUT/DELETE) защищены live RBAC enforcement с корректными 403-ответами\n   141→- **Поддерживающие метрики**:\n   142→  - RBAC check latency P95 → ≤ 10ms\n   143→  - Frontend role sync delay → ≤ 5 секунд\n   144→  - Audit log coverage → 100% ролевых операций\n   145→- **Контрольные метрики**:\n   146→  - Доля ошибок 500 при RBAC проверках → ≤ 0.1%\n   147→  - Polling endpoint availability → ≥ 99.5%\n   148→\n   149→## 4. Связанные ADR и артефакты\n   150→- `aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md` — данный PRD с требованиями\n   151→- `aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md` — выводы Researcher и рекомендации по интеграции\n   152→- `aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md` — контекстный пакет задачи\n   153→- FS-RBAC-03 specification — исходные требования спецификации RBAC\n   154→\n   155→## 5. Пользовательские сценарии\n   156→\n   157→### Сценарий 1: Администратор изменяет роль пользователя\n   158→1. Администратор вызывает API для изменения роли пользователя (PUT /api/users/{id}/role)\n   159→2. Система проверяет RBAC (только admin может менять роли) — возвращает 403 если нет прав\n   160→3. При успехе: роль обновляется в БД, операция записывается в audit_log\n   161→4. Frontend пользователя получает обновление при следующем polling-запросе (≤ 30s)\n   162→5. Zustand store обновляется и UI пересчитывает доступные действия без перезагрузки\n   163→\n   164→### Сценарий 2: Пользователь пытается выполнить запрещенное действие\n   165→1. Пользователь с ролью \"viewer\" пытается вызвать POST /api/resources\n   166→2. RBAC middleware проверяет X-Profile-Key headers — определяет недостаточно прав\n   167→3. API возвращает 403 Forbidden\n   168→4. Попытка записывается в audit_log (user_id, endpoint, timestamp, denied)\n   169→5. Frontend получает 403 и показывает сообщение о недостаточных правах\n   170→\n   171→### Сценарий 3: Сессия пользователя обновляется в реальном времени\n   172→1. Пользователь работает в приложении (React + Zustand)\n   173→2. Администратор отзывает роль через API\n   174→3. Frontend получает обновление при следующем polling-запросе\n   175→4. Zustand store обновляет auth state\n   176→5. UI скрывает элементы, требующие отозванной роли\n   177→\n   178→## 6. Требования\n   179→### 6.1 Функциональные\n   180→- [ ] Все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE) должны проходить RBAC проверку перед выполнением\n   181→- [ ] RBAC middleware должна интегрироваться с существующей X-Profile-Key header-based auth системой\n   182→- [ ] При отказе в доступе API возвращает 403 с информативным сообщением\n   183→- [ ] Audit-лог записывает: timestamp, user_id, action (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED), target_resource, role_changes\n   184→- [ ] Polling endpoint для получения обновлений ролей пользователя (каждые 30 секунд)\n   185→- [ ] Frontend Zustand store обрабатывает polling-ответы и обновляет auth state\n   186→- [ ] Role guards на frontend блокируют UI-элементы при отсутствии permissions\n   187→\n   188→### 6.2 Нефункциональные\n   189→- [ ] RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms (использовать in-memory caching с TTL)\n   190→- [ ] Polling endpoint availability ≥ 99.5%\n   191→- [ ] Audit log storage: отдельная таблица в БД с retention policy\n   192→- [ ] Graceful degradation: при недоступности polling endpoint frontend продолжает работу с текущей сессией\n   193→- [ ] Безопасность: audit-логи не должны содержать sensitive data (пароли, токены)\n   194→\n   195→### 6.3 Acceptance criteria\n   196→- [ ] AC-1: Все POST/PUT/DELETE API возвращают 403 для пользователей без необходимых ролей\n   197→- [ ] AC-2: Все операции изменения ролей (GRANT/REVOKE) логируются в audit_log таблицу\n   198→- [ ] AC-3: Frontend role guards обновляются в течение 30 секунд после изменения ролей в backend (polling interval)\n   199→- [ ] AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms под нагрузкой 1000 RPS\n   200→\n   201→## 7. Ограничения и зависимости\n   202→- **Технические**:\n   203→  - Интеграция с существующей X-Profile-Key header-based auth middleware (нельзя ломать обратную совместимость)\n   204→  - Polling endpoint должен масштабироваться с текущей инфраструктурой\n   205→  - Audit-логи хранятся в существующей БД (отдельная таблица)\n   206→  - Frontend: React + Zustand (текущий стек)\n   207→- **Процессные**:\n   208→  - Требуется согласование с security team по формату audit-логов\n   209→  - Релиз должен быть zero-downtime deployment\n   210→- **Внешние**: Нет внешних зависимостей (все компоненты внутренние)\n   211→\n   212→## 8. План и этапы\n   213→- **Майлстоуны**:\n   214→  - Phase 1: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging (MVP)\n   215→  - Phase 2: Polling endpoint implementation\n   216→  - Phase 3: Frontend polling integration + Zustand state sync\n   217→  - Phase 4: End-to-end testing + performance validation\n   218→- **Автоматизация и проверки**:\n   219→  - Unit tests для RBAC middleware\n   220→  - Integration tests для audit logging\n   221→  - Polling endpoint tests\n   222→  - Performance benchmarks (RBAC latency P95)\n   223→- **Системные интеграции**:\n   224→  - Backend: существующая JWT middleware, БД для audit_log\n   225→  - Frontend: Zustand store, polling client\n   226→  - Infrastructure: Polling endpoint (новый API endpoint)\n   227→\n   228→## 9. Риски и стратегии\n   229→| Риск | Вероятность/Импакт | Митигация |\n   230→|------|-------------------|-----------|\n   231→| Performance impact от live RBAC checks на каждый запрос | Средняя/Высокий | In-memory caching ролей с TTL; async audit logging |\n   232→| Session desync между backend и frontend | Средняя/Средний | Polling с 30s interval; manual refresh fallback |\n   233→| Audit log storage growth | Высокая/Средний | Retention policy (90 дней); архивирование в cold storage |\n   234→| Polling endpoint overload | Средняя/Высокий | Rate limiting; caching; horizontal scaling |\n   235→| Breaking changes в существующей auth middleware | Низкая/Высокий | Feature flags; canary deployment; rollback plan |\n   236→\n   237→## 10. Открытые вопросы\n   238→Все критические вопросы закрыты. Ответы зафиксированы в AIDD:DECISIONS.\n   239→\n   240→**Resolved:**\n   241→- Q1: Какие API требуют RBAC контроля → Решено: все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n   242→- Q2: Какая текущая реализация RBAC → Решено: X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n   243→- Q3: Какой frontend стек → Решено: React + Zustand (not Redux)\n   244→- Q4: Где хранить audit-логи → Решено: БД (отдельная таблица)\n   245→- Q5: Механизм синхронизации сессии → Решено: Polling (30s interval)\n   246→\n   247→## 11. PRD Review\n   248→Status: READY\n   249→\n   250→### Summary\n   251→All critical inconsistencies between analyst answers (Q1-Q5) and research findings have been resolved. PRD now correctly reflects: X-Profile-Key header-based auth, React + Zustand frontend, and polling-based session sync.\n   252→\n   253→### Findings — RESOLVED\n   254→- [x] **F1: Auth Model Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q2 updated to \"X-Profile-Key header-based auth\" (Q2=C). All PRD sections updated.\n   255→- [x] **F2: Frontend State Management Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q3 updated to \"React + Zustand\" (Q3=B). All PRD sections updated.\n   256→- [x] **F3: Real-time Infrastructure Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q5 updated to \"Polling\" (Q5=B) as simpler approach aligned with system constraints.\n   257→- [x] **F4: Research Status Warning** — **RESOLVED** — Research findings synchronized with PRD decisions.\n   258→- [x] **F5: AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS Not Cleared** — **RESOLVED** — All open questions closed, documented in section 10.\n   259→- [x] **F6: AIDD:ROLL_OUT Empty** — **RESOLVED** — Rollout plan filled with 4 phases, feature flags, and rollback strategies.\n   260→- [x] **F7: Research Hints Not Validated** — **RESOLVED** — Research hints validated against actual codebase structure.\n   261→\n   262→### Action items — COMPLETED\n   263→- [x] **AI-1: Update Q2 answer** — Changed Q2 from JWT-claims to X-Profile-Key header-based auth.\n   264→- [x] **AI-2: Update Q3 answer** — Changed Q3 from Redux to Zustand.\n   265→- [x] **AI-3: Revisit Q5 decision** — Changed Q5 from WebSocket to Polling (30s interval).\n   266→- [x] **AI-4: Sync research findings** — Research findings synchronized.\n   267→- [x] **AI-5: Fill rollout plan** — Rollout plan with phases and feature flags added to AIDD:ROLL_OUT.\n   268→- [x] **AI-6: Update PRD sections** — Sections 2, 6, 7, 8 synchronized with corrected answers.\n   269→\n   270→> Все пункты закрыты. Статус обновлён на `READY`.\n   271→\n   272→## 12. История изменений\n   273→- 2026-03-18 — Initial PRD draft based on analyst answers (Q1=B, Q2=B, Q3=A, Q4=A, Q5=A) — Analyst Agent\n   274→- 2026-03-18 — Updated all sections (1-10) with synthesized requirements, filled AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS, set Status to READY — Analyst Agent\n   275→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"289151de-a4db-4942-a0c0-3b3144dac800","uuid":"8b35193d-7c32-4f03-be4f-88769cb8b112","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md","content":"# PRD — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\nStatus: READY\nTicket: TST-001\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\n\n## Диалог analyst\n\nСсылка на исследование: `aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n\n\nВопрос 1 (Blocker): Какие конкретные API/эндпоинты считаются \"критическими\" для RBAC-контроля?\nЗачем: Определяет scope работы и какие middleware/декораторы нужно реализовать\nВарианты: A) Только админские эндпоинты (/admin/*) B) Все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE) C) Список из N конкретных эндпоинтов D) Все API с уровнем доступа > public\nDefault: B) Все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n**Ответ: B** — Все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE) требуют RBAC-контроля\n\nВопрос 2 (Clarification): Какая текущая реализация RBAC используется (библиотека или кастомное решение)?\nЗачем: Определяет архитектуру интеграции live enforcement — расширяем существующее или создаём новое\nВарианты: A) Casbin/OPA/другая библиотека B) Кастомная middleware на JWT-claims C) Ролевая проверка в каждом хендлере вручную D) RBAC отсутствует, нужно с нуля\nDefault: B) Кастомная middleware на JWT-claims\n**Ответ: C** — X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n\nВопрос 3 (Clarification): Какой фронтенд-фреймворк и текущий механизм аутентификации используется?\nЗачем: Определяет подход к синхронизации role guards без перезагрузки страницы\nВарианты: A) React + Context/Redux B) Vue + Pinia/Vuex C) Angular + Guards D) Другой (указать)\nDefault: A) React + Context/Redux\n**Ответ: B** — React + Zustand (not Redux)\n\nВопрос 4 (Clarification): Где должны храниться audit-логи ролевых операций?\nЗачем: Влияет на архитектуру логирования, retention policy и интеграции\nВарианты: A) База данных (отдельная таблица) B) Файловая система (JSONL/CSV) C) Внешний сервис (ELK/Splunk/Datadog) D) Гибрид: БД + архив в файл\nDefault: A) База данных (отдельная таблица)\n**Ответ: A** — База данных (отдельная таблица)\n\nВопрос 5 (Clarification): Какой механизм обновления сессии ожидается на фронтенде?\nЗачем: Определяет техническую реализацию live sync между backend и frontend\nВарианты: A) WebSocket (push-обновления) B) Polling (каждые N секунд) C) SSE (Server-Sent Events) D) Только на действиях пользователя (lazy update)\nDefault: A) WebSocket (push-обновления)\n**Ответ: B** — Polling (каждые N секунд) — simpler fallback approach\n\n<!-- Добавьте дополнительные «Вопрос N» по мере диалога. Ответы фиксируйте только в секции AIDD:ANSWERS. -->\n\n## AIDD:ANSWERS\n> Единый формат ответов из чата.\n\nAIDD:ANSWERS Q1=B; Q2=C; Q3=B; Q4=A; Q5=B\n\n## AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS\n- **Paths**: `src/middleware:src/auth:src/routes:frontend/src/guards:frontend/src/store:frontend/src/context:src/models:src/db/migrations`\n- **Keywords**: `RBAC,roles,permissions,roleGuard,requireRole,checkPermission,403,audit,session,middleware,JWT,claims,auth,redux,context,websocket,socket,push,notification,grant,revoke,denied,accessControl`\n- **Notes**:\n  1. Найти текущую JWT middleware и как она обрабатывает claims\n  2. Найти существующие role/permission checks в handlers\n  3. Найти frontend auth flow (Redux actions/reducers для auth)\n  4. Найти существующие route guards на frontend\n  5. Проверить polling requirements\n  6. Найти структуру БД для таблиц users, roles, permissions\n  7. Определить формат audit-логов если уже существуют\n\n## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n- FS-RBAC-03 spec requires live RBAC enforcement on critical API endpoints\n- Need to add audit logging for role operations and 403 responses\n- Frontend role guards must sync with session updates without page refresh\n- Ticket: TST-001\n\n## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n- All critical APIs must enforce RBAC with 403 on violations\n- Role operations must be auditable\n- Frontend must reflect role changes without refresh\n\n## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\nNone\n\n## AIDD:RISKS\n- Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\n- Session desync between backend/frontend → polling mechanism\n- Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\n\n## AIDD:DECISIONS\n- Live RBAC enforcement required per FS-RBAC-03 spec → compliance requirement\n- Frontend sync without refresh → UX requirement for seamless role updates\n- **Q1**: Critical APIs = все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n- **Q2**: Текущая реализация = X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n- **Q3**: Frontend = React + Zustand (not Redux)\n- **Q4**: Audit logs = база данных (отдельная таблица)\n- **Q5**: Session sync = Polling (fallback approach, simpler to implement)\n\n## AIDD:GOALS\n- Enforce live RBAC across critical APIs\n- Add auditable role operations trail\n- Synchronize frontend role guards with live session updates\n\n## AIDD:NON_GOALS\n- UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n- Migration of historical access logs\n- Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n\n## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n- AC-1: Critical APIs return 403 for unauthorized role access\n- AC-2: All role operations are logged with timestamp, user, action\n- AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of session change\n\n## AIDD:METRICS\n- RBAC check latency P95 → ≤ 10ms\n- Frontend role sync delay → ≤ 5 seconds\n- Audit log coverage → 100% of role operations\n\n## AIDD:ROLL_OUT\n- **Phase 1 (MVP)**: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging\n  - Feature flag: `rbac-enforcement-enabled` (default: false)\n  - Rollback: Disable flag to revert to legacy auth\n- **Phase 2**: Polling-based session sync\n  - Feature flag: `session-polling-enabled` (default: false)\n  - Rollback: Disable flag, frontend uses cached session only\n- **Phase 3**: Frontend role guards integration\n  - Feature flag: `live-role-guards` (default: false)\n  - Rollback: Revert to page-refresh session validation\n- **Phase 4**: End-to-end validation\n  - Load testing RBAC latency (target P95 ≤ 10ms)\n  - Monitor audit log storage growth\n  - Verify polling interval doesn't overload backend (target: 30s interval)\n\n## 1. Обзор\n- **Название продукта/фичи**: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n- **Исходные артефакты**: `aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`, `aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`, `aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n- **Дата/версия**: 2026-03-18 v1\n- **Краткое описание**: Реализация live RBAC enforcement для всех мутационных API (POST/PUT/DELETE), добавление аудит-логирования ролевых операций и 403-ответов, синхронизация frontend role guards с backend-сессией через polling (30s interval) без перезагрузки страницы.\n\n## 2. Контекст и проблемы\n- **Текущая ситуация**: Система использует X-Profile-Key header-based auth middleware для RBAC, но live enforcement не реализован для всех критических API. Frontend на React + Zustand не получает live-обновлений при изменении ролей пользователя. Audit-логи ролевых операций отсутствуют.\n- **Проблемы/гипотезы**:\n  1. Нет единой точки контроля RBAC для всех мутационных API — потенциальные security gaps\n  2. Frontend не синхронизируется с изменениями ролей в реальном времени — пользователи видят устаревшие permissions\n  3. Отсутствие audit trail для ролевых операций — невозможно отследить кто и когда получил/потерял доступ\n  4. 403-ответы не логируются — сложно анализировать попытки несанкционированного доступа\n- **Затронутые сегменты**: Все аутентифицированные пользователи системы (100%), администраторы управляющие ролями\n\n## 3. Цели и метрики успеха\n- **North Star / основная метрика**: 100% мутационных API (POST/PUT/DELETE) защищены live RBAC enforcement с корректными 403-ответами\n- **Поддерживающие метрики**:\n  - RBAC check latency P95 → ≤ 10ms\n  - Frontend role sync delay → ≤ 5 секунд\n  - Audit log coverage → 100% ролевых операций\n- **Контрольные метрики**:\n  - Доля ошибок 500 при RBAC проверках → ≤ 0.1%\n  - Polling endpoint availability → ≥ 99.5%\n\n## 4. Связанные ADR и артефакты\n- `aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md` — данный PRD с требованиями\n- `aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md` — выводы Researcher и рекомендации по интеграции\n- `aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md` — контекстный пакет задачи\n- FS-RBAC-03 specification — исходные требования спецификации RBAC\n\n## 5. Пользовательские сценарии\n\n### Сценарий 1: Администратор изменяет роль пользователя\n1. Администратор вызывает API для изменения роли пользователя (PUT /api/users/{id}/role)\n2. Система проверяет RBAC (только admin может менять роли) — возвращает 403 если нет прав\n3. При успехе: роль обновляется в БД, операция записывается в audit_log\n4. Frontend пользователя получает обновление при следующем polling-запросе (≤ 30s)\n5. Zustand store обновляется и UI пересчитывает доступные действия без перезагрузки\n\n### Сценарий 2: Пользователь пытается выполнить запрещенное действие\n1. Пользователь с ролью \"viewer\" пытается вызвать POST /api/resources\n2. RBAC middleware проверяет X-Profile-Key headers — определяет недостаточно прав\n3. API возвращает 403 Forbidden\n4. Попытка записывается в audit_log (user_id, endpoint, timestamp, denied)\n5. Frontend получает 403 и показывает сообщение о недостаточных правах\n\n### Сценарий 3: Сессия пользователя обновляется в реальном времени\n1. Пользователь работает в приложении (React + Zustand)\n2. Администратор отзывает роль через API\n3. Frontend получает обновление при следующем polling-запросе\n4. Zustand store обновляет auth state\n5. UI скрывает элементы, требующие отозванной роли\n\n## 6. Требования\n### 6.1 Функциональные\n- [ ] Все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE) должны проходить RBAC проверку перед выполнением\n- [ ] RBAC middleware должна интегрироваться с существующей X-Profile-Key header-based auth системой\n- [ ] При отказе в доступе API возвращает 403 с информативным сообщением\n- [ ] Audit-лог записывает: timestamp, user_id, action (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED), target_resource, role_changes\n- [ ] Polling endpoint для получения обновлений ролей пользователя (каждые 30 секунд)\n- [ ] Frontend Zustand store обрабатывает polling-ответы и обновляет auth state\n- [ ] Role guards на frontend блокируют UI-элементы при отсутствии permissions\n\n### 6.2 Нефункциональные\n- [ ] RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms (использовать in-memory caching с TTL)\n- [ ] Polling endpoint availability ≥ 99.5%\n- [ ] Audit log storage: отдельная таблица в БД с retention policy\n- [ ] Graceful degradation: при недоступности polling endpoint frontend продолжает работу с текущей сессией\n- [ ] Безопасность: audit-логи не должны содержать sensitive data (пароли, токены)\n\n### 6.3 Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] AC-1: Все POST/PUT/DELETE API возвращают 403 для пользователей без необходимых ролей\n- [ ] AC-2: Все операции изменения ролей (GRANT/REVOKE) логируются в audit_log таблицу\n- [ ] AC-3: Frontend role guards обновляются в течение 30 секунд после изменения ролей в backend (polling interval)\n- [ ] AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms под нагрузкой 1000 RPS\n\n## 7. Ограничения и зависимости\n- **Технические**:\n  - Интеграция с существующей X-Profile-Key header-based auth middleware (нельзя ломать обратную совместимость)\n  - Polling endpoint должен масштабироваться с текущей инфраструктурой\n  - Audit-логи хранятся в существующей БД (отдельная таблица)\n  - Frontend: React + Zustand (текущий стек)\n- **Процессные**:\n  - Требуется согласование с security team по формату audit-логов\n  - Релиз должен быть zero-downtime deployment\n- **Внешние**: Нет внешних зависимостей (все компоненты внутренние)\n\n## 8. План и этапы\n- **Майлстоуны**:\n  - Phase 1: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging (MVP)\n  - Phase 2: Polling endpoint implementation\n  - Phase 3: Frontend polling integration + Zustand state sync\n  - Phase 4: End-to-end testing + performance validation\n- **Автоматизация и проверки**:\n  - Unit tests для RBAC middleware\n  - Integration tests для audit logging\n  - Polling endpoint tests\n  - Performance benchmarks (RBAC latency P95)\n- **Системные интеграции**:\n  - Backend: существующая JWT middleware, БД для audit_log\n  - Frontend: Zustand store, polling client\n  - Infrastructure: Polling endpoint (новый API endpoint)\n\n## 9. Риски и стратегии\n| Риск | Вероятность/Импакт | Митигация |\n|------|-------------------|-----------|\n| Performance impact от live RBAC checks на каждый запрос | Средняя/Высокий | In-memory caching ролей с TTL; async audit logging |\n| Session desync между backend и frontend | Средняя/Средний | Polling с 30s interval; manual refresh fallback |\n| Audit log storage growth | Высокая/Средний | Retention policy (90 дней); архивирование в cold storage |\n| Polling endpoint overload | Средняя/Высокий | Rate limiting; caching; horizontal scaling |\n| Breaking changes в существующей auth middleware | Низкая/Высокий | Feature flags; canary deployment; rollback plan |\n\n## 10. Открытые вопросы\nВсе критические вопросы закрыты. Ответы зафиксированы в AIDD:DECISIONS.\n\n**Resolved:**\n- Q1: Какие API требуют RBAC контроля → Решено: все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n- Q2: Какая текущая реализация RBAC → Решено: X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n- Q3: Какой frontend стек → Решено: React + Zustand (not Redux)\n- Q4: Где хранить audit-логи → Решено: БД (отдельная таблица)\n- Q5: Механизм синхронизации сессии → Решено: Polling (30s interval)\n\n## 11. PRD Review\nStatus: READY\n\n### Summary\nAll critical inconsistencies between analyst answers (Q1-Q5) and research findings have been resolved. PRD now correctly reflects: X-Profile-Key header-based auth, React + Zustand frontend, and polling-based session sync.\n\n### Findings — RESOLVED\n- [x] **F1: Auth Model Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q2 updated to \"X-Profile-Key header-based auth\" (Q2=C). All PRD sections updated.\n- [x] **F2: Frontend State Management Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q3 updated to \"React + Zustand\" (Q3=B). All PRD sections updated.\n- [x] **F3: Real-time Infrastructure Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q5 updated to \"Polling\" (Q5=B) as simpler approach aligned with system constraints.\n- [x] **F4: Research Status Warning** — **RESOLVED** — Research findings synchronized with PRD decisions.\n- [x] **F5: AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS Not Cleared** — **RESOLVED** — All open questions closed, documented in section 10.\n- [x] **F6: AIDD:ROLL_OUT Empty** — **RESOLVED** — Rollout plan filled with 4 phases, feature flags, and rollback strategies.\n- [x] **F7: Research Hints Not Validated** — **RESOLVED** — Research hints validated against actual codebase structure.\n\n### Action items — COMPLETED\n- [x] **AI-1: Update Q2 answer** — Changed Q2 from JWT-claims to X-Profile-Key header-based auth.\n- [x] **AI-2: Update Q3 answer** — Changed Q3 from Redux to Zustand.\n- [x] **AI-3: Revisit Q5 decision** — Changed Q5 from WebSocket to Polling (30s interval).\n- [x] **AI-4: Sync research findings** — Research findings synchronized.\n- [x] **AI-5: Fill rollout plan** — Rollout plan with phases and feature flags added to AIDD:ROLL_OUT.\n- [x] **AI-6: Update PRD sections** — Sections 2, 6, 7, 8 synchronized with corrected answers.\n\n> Все пункты закрыты. Статус обновлён на `READY`.\n\n## 12. История изменений\n- 2026-03-18 — Initial PRD draft based on analyst answers (Q1=B, Q2=B, Q3=A, Q4=A, Q5=A) — Analyst Agent\n- 2026-03-18 — Updated all sections (1-10) with synthesized requirements, filled AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS, set Status to READY — Analyst Agent\n","numLines":275,"startLine":1,"totalLines":275}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_f5MQLTsO9Z3WzSBvkDZ3Rq9n","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Implementation Plan — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n     2→\n     3→**Status:** READY\n     4→**Ticket:** TST-001\n     5→**Updated:** 2026-03-18\n     6→**Research Status:** warn (see research findings for PRD overrides)\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## Executive Summary\n    11→\n    12→This plan implements live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and frontend role synchronization. Based on research findings, we adapt the PRD assumptions to the actual codebase:\n    13→\n    14→| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Adaptation |\n    15→|----------------|------------------|------------|\n    16→| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom WebFlux filter with header parsing |\n    17→| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend Zustand store with SSE listener |\n    18→| WebSocket push | SSE already exists for flows | Extend SSE for role notifications |\n    19→| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters (no Spring Security) |\n    20→\n    21→---\n    22→\n    23→## AIDD:DECISIONS\n    24→\n    25→### Architecture Decisions\n    26→\n    27→1. **No Spring Security** — Adding spring-boot-starter-security introduces significant complexity and potential conflicts with existing WebFlux setup. Instead, implement custom `WebFilter` for RBAC.\n    28→\n    29→2. **Extend SSE instead of WebSocket** — SSE infrastructure already exists (`subscribeToFlowEvents` in apiClient.ts). Adding WebSocket requires new dependencies and infrastructure. SSE is sufficient for unidirectional server-to-client role updates.\n    30→\n    31→3. **Role Caching with Caffeine** — Backend uses Caffeine cache (already in classpath). Cache profile roles with 5-minute TTL to meet P95 ≤ 10ms latency requirement.\n    32→\n    33→4. **Audit Log as Separate Table** — Follow existing pattern (note_entry table) with PostgreSQL JSONB for flexible metadata.\n    34→\n    35→5. **Header-Based Identity** — Use `X-Profile-Key` (format: `namespace:reference`) and `X-Profile-Auth` headers for identity extraction.\n    36→\n    37→---\n    38→\n    39→## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n    40→\n    41→- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must return 403 for unauthorized requests\n    42→- Audit log must capture: timestamp, actor profile key, action (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED), target resource, result\n    43→- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of backend role change\n    44→- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n    45→- Zero breaking changes to existing API contracts\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## AIDD:RISKS\n    50→\n    51→| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n    52→|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|------------|\n    53→| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Circuit breaker; fail-closed; cache roles |\n    54→| R-002 | Cache stale roles after assignment | Medium | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change; TTL 5min |\n    55→| R-003 | SSE connection memory leak | Low | Medium | Proper cleanup on disconnect; subscriber limits |\n    56→| R-004 | Audit log write failures | Low | Medium | Async logging; error queue; never block request |\n    57→| R-005 | RBAC filter performance degradation | Low | High | Caffeine cache; async audit; P95 target 10ms |\n    58→| R-006 | Breaking change to existing APIs | Low | High | Feature flags; audit-only mode first; rollback |\n    59→| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High | Add to all profile configs; verify on startup |\n    60→| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High | Define contract; implement fallback to local DB |\n    61→\n    62→### Validation-Derived Risks (from TST-001-validation.md)\n    63→\n    64→**R-007: Component Scan Configuration**\n    65→The application uses profile-based component scanning. The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.\n    66→- **Mitigation**: Create `RbacConfig.java` with `@Profile(\"!test\")` active in all non-test profiles\n    67→\n    68→**R-008: Profile Service Integration**\n    69→The plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles was found in research.\n    70→- **Mitigation**: Define profile service contract or implement local role storage via `rbac_profile_roles` table\n    71→\n    72→---\n    73→\n    74→## Milestones & Iterations\n    75→\n    76→### Phase 1: Backend Foundation (Days 1-3)\n    77→**Goal:** Core RBAC filter and audit infrastructure\n    78→\n    79→#### 1.1 Database Migration\n    80→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml`\n    81→\n    82→```yaml\n    83→# Create audit_log table\n    84→- changeSet:\n    85→    id: rbac-0001-audit-log\n    86→    author: ai-advent\n    87→    context: rbac\n    88→    changes:\n    89→      - createTable:\n    90→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n    91→          columns:\n    92→            - column:\n    93→                name: id\n    94→                type: UUID\n    95→                defaultValueComputed: gen_random_uuid()\n    96→                constraints:\n    97→                  primaryKey: true\n    98→            - column:\n    99→                name: timestamp\n   100→                type: TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE\n   101→                defaultValueComputed: now()\n   102→                constraints:\n   103→                  nullable: false\n   104→            - column:\n   105→                name: actor_namespace\n   106→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   107→                constraints:\n   108→                  nullable: false\n   109→            - column:\n   110→                name: actor_reference\n   111→                type: VARCHAR(128)\n   112→                constraints:\n   113→                  nullable: false\n   114→            - column:\n   115→                name: action\n   116→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   117→                constraints:\n   118→                  nullable: false\n   119→            - column:\n   120→                name: target_resource\n   121→                type: VARCHAR(256)\n   122→            - column:\n   123→                name: target_profile_namespace\n   124→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   125→            - column:\n   126→                name: target_profile_reference\n   127→                type: VARCHAR(128)\n   128→            - column:\n   129→                name: result\n   130→                type: VARCHAR(16)\n   131→                constraints:\n   132→                  nullable: false\n   133→            - column:\n   134→                name: http_method\n   135→                type: VARCHAR(8)\n   136→            - column:\n   137→                name: http_path\n   138→                type: VARCHAR(512)\n   139→            - column:\n   140→                name: metadata\n   141→                type: JSONB\n   142→      - createIndex:\n   143→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n   144→          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_timestamp\n   145→          columns:\n   146→            - column:\n   147→                name: timestamp\n   148→      - createIndex:\n   149→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n   150→          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_actor\n   151→          columns:\n   152→            - column:\n   153→                name: actor_namespace\n   154→            - column:\n   155→                name: actor_reference\n   156→```\n   157→\n   158→#### 1.2 RBAC Core Domain\n   159→**Files to create:**\n   160→\n   161→| File | Purpose |\n   162→|------|---------|\n   163→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Enum: ADMIN, USER, VIEWER, etc. |\n   164→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Value object: namespace + reference |\n   165→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Enum: READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN |\n   166→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Record: allowed (boolean), reason (string) |\n   167→\n   168→#### 1.3 RBAC Filter (WebFlux)\n   169→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java`\n   170→\n   171→```java\n   172→@Component\n   173→@Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100) // After logging, before business logic\n   174→public class RbacWebFilter implements WebFilter {\n   175→\n   176→    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   177→    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n   178→    private final RbacPathMatcher pathMatcher;\n   179→\n   180→    @Override\n   181→    public Mono<Void> filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {\n   182→        HttpMethod method = exchange.getRequest().getMethod();\n   183→        String path = exchange.getRequest().getPath().value();\n   184→\n   185→        // Skip non-mutation methods\n   186→        if (!isMutationMethod(method)) {\n   187→            return chain.filter(exchange);\n   188→        }\n   189→\n   190→        // Skip excluded paths (health, public APIs)\n   191→        if (pathMatcher.isPublicPath(path)) {\n   192→            return chain.filter(exchange);\n   193→        }\n   194→\n   195→        // Extract identity from headers\n   196→        ProfileIdentity identity = extractIdentity(exchange.getRequest());\n   197→        if (identity == null) {\n   198→            return auditAndDeny(exchange, null, path, method, \"Missing identity headers\");\n   199→        }\n   200→\n   201→        // Check required roles for path\n   202→        Set<Role> requiredRoles = pathMatcher.getRequiredRoles(path, method);\n   203→\n   204→        return roleService.hasAnyRole(identity, requiredRoles)\n   205→            .flatMap(hasRole -> {\n   206→                if (hasRole) {\n   207→                    auditService.logAccess(identity, path, method, \"ALLOWED\");\n   208→                    return chain.filter(exchange);\n   209→                } else {\n   210→                    return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"Insufficient permissions\");\n   211→                }\n   212→            })\n   213→            .onErrorResume(e -> {\n   214→                log.error(\"RBAC check failed\", e);\n   215→                return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"RBAC error: \" + e.getMessage());\n   216→            });\n   217→    }\n   218→\n   219→    private Mono<Void> auditAndDeny(ServerWebExchange exchange, ProfileIdentity identity,\n   220→                                     String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n   221→        auditService.logDenied(identity, path, method, reason);\n   222→        exchange.getResponse().setStatusCode(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);\n   223→        exchange.getResponse().getHeaders().setContentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);\n   224→        String body = String.format(\"{\\\"error\\\":\\\"Forbidden\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"%s\\\"}\", reason);\n   225→        DataBuffer buffer = exchange.getResponse().bufferFactory().wrap(body.getBytes());\n   226→        return exchange.getResponse().writeWith(Mono.just(buffer));\n   227→    }\n   228→}\n   229→```\n   230→\n   231→#### 1.4 Profile Role Service with Caching\n   232→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java`\n   233→\n   234→```java\n   235→@Service\n   236→public class ProfileRoleService {\n   237→\n   238→    private final LoadingCache<ProfileIdentity, Set<Role>> roleCache;\n   239→    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n   240→\n   241→    public ProfileRoleService(ProfileClient profileClient,\n   242→                              @Value(\"${rbac.cache.ttl-minutes:5}\") int cacheTtlMinutes) {\n   243→        this.profileClient = profileClient;\n   244→        this.roleCache = Caffeine.newBuilder()\n   245→            .expireAfterWrite(cacheTtlMinutes, TimeUnit.MINUTES)\n   246→            .maximumSize(10_000)\n   247→            .recordStats()\n   248→            .build(this::loadRoles);\n   249→    }\n   250→\n   251→    private Set<Role> loadRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   252→        return profileClient.fetchRoles(identity);\n   253→    }\n   254→\n   255→    public Mono<Boolean> hasAnyRole(ProfileIdentity identity, Set<Role> requiredRoles) {\n   256→        if (requiredRoles.isEmpty()) {\n   257→            return Mono.just(true);\n   258→        }\n   259→        return Mono.fromCallable(() -> roleCache.get(identity))\n   260→            .subscribeOn(Schedulers.boundedElastic())\n   261→            .map(userRoles -> userRoles.stream().anyMatch(requiredRoles::contains));\n   262→    }\n   263→\n   264→    public void invalidateCache(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   265→        roleCache.invalidate(identity);\n   266→    }\n   267→\n   268→    public CacheStats getCacheStats() {\n   269→        return roleCache.stats();\n   270→    }\n   271→}\n   272→```\n   273→\n   274→#### 1.5 Audit Log Service\n   275→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java`\n   276→\n   277→```java\n   278→@Service\n   279→public class AuditLogService {\n   280→\n   281→    private final AuditLogRepository repository;\n   282→    private final ExecutorService asyncExecutor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);\n   283→\n   284→    public void logAccess(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String result) {\n   285→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   286→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   287→            entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n   288→            entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n   289→            entry.setAction(\"ACCESS\");\n   290→            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n   291→            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n   292→            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n   293→            entry.setResult(result);\n   294→            repository.save(entry);\n   295→        });\n   296→    }\n   297→\n   298→    public void logDenied(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n   299→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   300→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   301→            if (identity != null) {\n   302→                entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n   303→                entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n   304→            }\n   305→            entry.setAction(\"DENIED\");\n   306→            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n   307→            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n   308→            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n   309→            entry.setResult(\"DENIED\");\n   310→            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"reason\", reason));\n   311→            repository.save(entry);\n   312→        });\n   313→    }\n   314→\n   315→    public void logRoleChange(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target,\n   316→                              String action, Set<Role> roles) {\n   317→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   318→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   319→            entry.setActorNamespace(actor.namespace());\n   320→            entry.setActorReference(actor.reference());\n   321→            entry.setAction(action); // GRANT or REVOKE\n   322→            entry.setTargetProfileNamespace(target.namespace());\n   323→            entry.setTargetProfileReference(target.reference());\n   324→            entry.setResult(\"SUCCESS\");\n   325→            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"roles\", roles));\n   326→            repository.save(entry);\n   327→        });\n   328→    }\n   329→\n   330→    private void asyncLog(Runnable task) {\n   331→        asyncExecutor.submit(() -> {\n   332→            try {\n   333→                task.run();\n   334→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   335→                log.error(\"Failed to write audit log\", e);\n   336→            }\n   337→        });\n   338→    }\n   339→}\n   340→```\n   341→\n   342→#### 1.6 Audit Log Entity & Repository\n   343→**Files:**\n   344→- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java`\n   345→- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java`\n   346→\n   347→---\n   348→\n   349→### Phase 2: Profile Service Integration (Days 4-5)\n   350→**Goal:** Connect to existing profile service for role resolution\n   351→\n   352→#### 2.1 Profile Client\n   353→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java`\n   354→\n   355→```java\n   356→@Component\n   357→public class ProfileClient {\n   358→\n   359→    private final WebClient webClient;\n   360→    private final String profileServiceUrl;\n   361→\n   362→    public ProfileClient(@Value(\"${profile.service.url}\") String profileServiceUrl,\n   363→                         WebClient.Builder webClientBuilder) {\n   364→        this.profileServiceUrl = profileServiceUrl;\n   365→        this.webClient = webClientBuilder.baseUrl(profileServiceUrl).build();\n   366→    }\n   367→\n   368→    public Set<Role> fetchRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   369→        try {\n   370→            ProfileResponse response = webClient.get()\n   371→                .uri(\"/api/profiles/{namespace}/{reference}\", identity.namespace(), identity.reference())\n   372→                .retrieve()\n   373→                .bodyToMono(ProfileResponse.class)\n   374→                .timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(2))\n   375→                .block();\n   376→\n   377→            return response != null && response.roles() != null\n   378→                ? response.roles().stream().map(Role::valueOf).collect(Collectors.toSet())\n   379→                : Set.of();\n   380→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   381→            log.error(\"Failed to fetch roles for {}\", identity, e);\n   382→            // Fail-closed: return empty set (deny access)\n   383→            return Set.of();\n   384→        }\n   385→    }\n   386→}\n   387→```\n   388→\n   389→#### 2.2 Profile Response DTO\n   390→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java`\n   391→\n   392→```java\n   393→public record ProfileResponse(\n   394→    String profileId,\n   395→    String namespace,\n   396→    String reference,\n   397→    List<String> roles,\n   398→    Instant updatedAt\n   399→) {}\n   400→```\n   401→\n   402→#### 2.3 RBAC Configuration\n   403→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java`\n   404→\n   405→```java\n   406→@Configuration\n   407→@EnableConfigurationProperties(RbacProperties.class)\n   408→public class RbacConfiguration {\n   409→\n   410→    @Bean\n   411→    public RbacPathMatcher rbacPathMatcher(RbacProperties properties) {\n   412→        return new RbacPathMatcher(properties);\n   413→    }\n   414→}\n   415→```\n   416→\n   417→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java`\n   418→\n   419→```java\n   420→@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = \"rbac\")\n   421→public record RbacProperties(\n   422→    List<PathRule> protectedPaths,\n   423→    List<String> publicPaths,\n   424→    int cacheTtlMinutes\n   425→) {\n   426→    public record PathRule(\n   427→        String path,\n   428→        Set<String> methods,\n   429→        Set<String> requiredRoles\n   430→    ) {}\n   431→}\n   432→```\n   433→\n   434→---\n   435→\n   436→### Phase 3: Frontend Role Sync (Days 6-8)\n   437→**Goal:** Real-time role synchronization via SSE\n   438→\n   439→#### 3.1 Extend Profile Store with SSE\n   440→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n   441→\n   442→```typescript\n   443→// Add to ProfileStoreState\n   444→type ProfileStoreState = {\n   445→  // ... existing fields\n   446→  roleVersion: number; // Incremented on role change\n   447→  lastRoleSync: string | null;\n   448→  subscribeToRoleChanges: () => () => void;\n   449→};\n   450→\n   451→// Add to store implementation\n   452→export const useProfileStore = create<ProfileStoreState>()(\n   453→  persist(\n   454→    (set, get) => ({\n   455→      // ... existing initial state\n   456→      roleVersion: 0,\n   457→      lastRoleSync: null,\n   458→\n   459→      subscribeToRoleChanges: () => {\n   460→        const { namespace, reference, channel, devToken } = getActiveProfileSelection();\n   461→        if (!namespace || !reference) return () => {};\n   462→\n   463→        const params = new URLSearchParams();\n   464→        params.set('namespace', namespace);\n   465→        params.set('reference', reference);\n   466→        if (channel) params.set('channel', channel);\n   467→        if (devToken) params.set('token', devToken);\n   468→\n   469→        const eventSource = new EventSource(\n   470→          `${API_BASE_URL}/api/profiles/role-events?${params.toString()}`\n   471→        );\n   472→\n   473→        eventSource.addEventListener('role-change', (event) => {\n   474→          const data = JSON.parse(event.data);\n   475→          set((state) => ({\n   476→            profile: state.profile ? {\n   477→              ...state.profile,\n   478→              roles: data.roles,\n   479→              updatedAt: data.timestamp,\n   480→            } : null,\n   481→            roleVersion: state.roleVersion + 1,\n   482→            lastRoleSync: new Date().toISOString(),\n   483→          }));\n   484→        });\n   485→\n   486→        eventSource.onerror = () => {\n   487→          // Auto-reconnect handled by browser, but we log it\n   488→          console.warn('Role events connection error, will retry...');\n   489→        };\n   490→\n   491→        return () => eventSource.close();\n   492→      },\n   493→    }),\n   494→    // ... existing persist config\n   495→  ),\n   496→);\n   497→```\n   498→\n   499→#### 3.2 Create useRoleGuard Hook\n   500→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n   501→\n   502→```typescript\n   503→import { useEffect, useMemo } from 'react';\n   504→import { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n   505→\n   506→export function useRoleGuard(requiredRole?: string) {\n   507→  const roles = useProfileStore((state) => state.profile?.roles ?? []);\n   508→  const roleVersion = useProfileStore((state) => state.roleVersion);\n   509→\n   510→  // Subscribe to role changes on mount\n   511→  useEffect(() => {\n   512→    const unsubscribe = useProfileStore.getState().subscribeToRoleChanges();\n   513→    return unsubscribe;\n   514→  }, []);\n   515→\n   516→  const hasRole = useMemo(() => {\n   517→    if (!requiredRole) return true;\n   518→    return roles.some((role) => role === requiredRole);\n   519→  }, [roles, requiredRole, roleVersion]);\n   520→\n   521→  const hasAnyRole = useMemo(() => {\n   522→    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roles.some((role) => roleCodes.includes(role));\n   523→  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n   524→\n   525→  const hasAllRoles = useMemo(() => {\n   526→    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roleCodes.every((role) => roles.includes(role));\n   527→  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n   528→\n   529→  return {\n   530→    roles,\n   531→    hasRole,\n   532→    hasAnyRole,\n   533→    hasAllRoles,\n   534→    isAdmin: roles.includes('admin'),\n   535→    roleVersion,\n   536→  };\n   537→}\n   538→```\n   539→\n   540→#### 3.3 Update AdminRoles Page\n   541→**File:** `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n   542→\n   543→Replace inline role check with hook:\n   544→\n   545→```typescript\n   546→// Replace lines 34-36:\n   547→const { isAdmin } = useRoleGuard('admin');\n   548→\n   549→// Replace hasAdminRole references with isAdmin\n   550→```\n   551→\n   552→#### 3.4 Create RoleGuard Component\n   553→**File:** `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n   554→\n   555→```typescript\n   556→import React from 'react';\n   557→import { useRoleGuard } from '../lib/useRoleGuard';\n   558→\n   559→interface RoleGuardProps {\n   560→  requiredRole: string;\n   561→  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n   562→  children: React.ReactNode;\n   563→}\n   564→\n   565→export const RoleGuard: React.FC<RoleGuardProps> = ({\n   566→  requiredRole,\n   567→  fallback = null,\n   568→  children,\n   569→}) => {\n   570→  const { hasRole } = useRoleGuard(requiredRole);\n   571→  return hasRole ? <>{children}</> : <>{fallback}</>;\n   572→};\n   573→\n   574→interface AdminGuardProps {\n   575→  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n   576→  children: React.ReactNode;\n   577→}\n   578→\n   579→export const AdminGuard: React.FC<AdminGuardProps> = ({ fallback, children }) => (\n   580→  <RoleGuard requiredRole=\"admin\" fallback={fallback}>\n   581→    {children}\n   582→  </RoleGuard>\n   583→);\n   584→```\n   585→\n   586→---\n   587→\n   588→### Phase 4: SSE Role Events Endpoint (Days 9-10)\n   589→**Goal:** Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications\n   590→\n   591→#### 4.1 Role Event Service\n   592→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java`\n   593→\n   594→```java\n   595→@Service\n   596→public class RoleEventService {\n   597→\n   598→    private final Map<ProfileIdentity, Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent>> subscribers = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();\n   599→\n   600→    public Flux<RoleChangeEvent> subscribe(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   601→        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = Sinks.many().multicast().onBackpressureBuffer();\n   602→        subscribers.put(identity, sink);\n   603→\n   604→        return sink.asFlux()\n   605→            .doOnCancel(() -> subscribers.remove(identity))\n   606→            .doOnTerminate(() -> subscribers.remove(identity));\n   607→    }\n   608→\n   609→    public void notifyRoleChange(ProfileIdentity identity, List<String> roles) {\n   610→        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = subscribers.get(identity);\n   611→        if (sink != null) {\n   612→            sink.tryEmitNext(new RoleChangeEvent(roles, Instant.now()));\n   613→        }\n   614→    }\n   615→\n   616→    public void broadcastRoleChange(ProfileIdentity target, List<String> roles) {\n   617→        notifyRoleChange(target, roles);\n   618→    }\n   619→\n   620→    public record RoleChangeEvent(List<String> roles, Instant timestamp) {}\n   621→}\n   622→```\n   623→\n   624→#### 4.2 SSE Controller\n   625→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java`\n   626→\n   627→```java\n   628→@RestController\n   629→@RequestMapping(\"/api/profiles\")\n   630→public class RoleEventsController {\n   631→\n   632→    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n   633→\n   634→    @GetMapping(value = \"/role-events\", produces = MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)\n   635→    public Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> roleEvents(\n   636→            @RequestParam String namespace,\n   637→            @RequestParam String reference,\n   638→            @RequestParam(required = false) String channel,\n   639→            @RequestParam(required = false) String token) {\n   640→\n   641→        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(namespace, reference);\n   642→\n   643→        return eventService.subscribe(identity)\n   644→            .map(event -> ServerSentEvent.builder(event)\n   645→                .event(\"role-change\")\n   646→                .id(UUID.randomUUID().toString())\n   647→                .build())\n   648→            .mergeWith(heartbeatFlux());\n   649→    }\n   650→\n   651→    private Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> heartbeatFlux() {\n   652→        return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(30))\n   653→            .map(i -> ServerSentEvent.<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>builder()\n   654→                .comment(\"heartbeat\")\n   655→                .build());\n   656→    }\n   657→}\n   658→```\n   659→\n   660→#### 4.3 Integrate with Admin Role Operations\n   661→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java`\n   662→\n   663→```java\n   664→@Service\n   665→public class RoleAssignmentService {\n   666→\n   667→    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n   668→    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n   669→    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n   670→    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   671→\n   672→    public Mono<Void> assignRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n   673→        return profileClient.assignRole(target, role)\n   674→            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n   675→                // Invalidate cache\n   676→                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n   677→                // Notify user\n   678→                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n   679→                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n   680→                // Audit\n   681→                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"GRANT\", Set.of(role));\n   682→            });\n   683→    }\n   684→\n   685→    public Mono<Void> revokeRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n   686→        return profileClient.revokeRole(target, role)\n   687→            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n   688→                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n   689→                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n   690→                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n   691→                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"REVOKE\", Set.of(role));\n   692→            });\n   693→    }\n   694→}\n   695→```\n   696→\n   697→---\n   698→\n   699→### Phase 5: Testing & Validation (Days 11-12)\n   700→**Goal:** Comprehensive test coverage\n   701→\n   702→#### 5.1 Backend Tests\n   703→\n   704→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilterTest.java`\n   705→\n   706→```java\n   707→@WebFluxTest(RbacWebFilter.class)\n   708→class RbacWebFilterTest {\n   709→\n   710→    @MockBean\n   711→    private ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   712→\n   713→    @MockBean\n   714→    private AuditLogService auditService;\n   715→\n   716→    @Autowired\n   717→    private WebTestClient webClient;\n   718→\n   719→    @Test\n   720→    void shouldAllowGetRequestWithoutRole() {\n   721→        webClient.get().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   722→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n   723→            .exchange()\n   724→            .expectStatus().isOk();\n   725→    }\n   726→\n   727→    @Test\n   728→    void shouldDenyPostWithoutRole() {\n   729→        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(false));\n   730→\n   731→        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   732→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n   733→            .exchange()\n   734→            .expectStatus().isForbidden();\n   735→\n   736→        verify(auditService).logDenied(any(), eq(\"/api/test\"), eq(HttpMethod.POST), any());\n   737→    }\n   738→\n   739→    @Test\n   740→    void shouldAllowPostWithAdminRole() {\n   741→        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(true));\n   742→\n   743→        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   744→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:admin\")\n   745→            .exchange()\n   746→            .expectStatus().isOk();\n   747→    }\n   748→}\n   749→```\n   750→\n   751→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleServiceTest.java`\n   752→\n   753→```java\n   754→class ProfileRoleServiceTest {\n   755→\n   756→    @Test\n   757→    void shouldCacheRoles() {\n   758→        // First call hits profile service\n   759→        // Second call uses cache\n   760→        // Verify cache stats\n   761→    }\n   762→\n   763→    @Test\n   764→    void shouldFailClosedOnError() {\n   765→        // When profile service unavailable\n   766→        // Return empty roles (deny access)\n   767→    }\n   768→}\n   769→```\n   770→\n   771→#### 5.2 Frontend Tests\n   772→\n   773→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` (new)\n   774→\n   775→```typescript\n   776→import { renderHook, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';\n   777→import { useRoleGuard } from './useRoleGuard';\n   778→import { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n   779→\n   780→describe('useRoleGuard', () => {\n   781→  it('should update when roles change', async () => {\n   782→    const { result } = renderHook(() => useRoleGuard('admin'));\n   783→\n   784→    expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(false);\n   785→\n   786→    // Simulate role change event\n   787→    useProfileStore.setState({\n   788→      profile: { roles: ['admin'] } as UserProfileDocument,\n   789→      roleVersion: 1,\n   790→    });\n   791→\n   792→    await waitFor(() => {\n   793→      expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(true);\n   794→    });\n   795→  });\n   796→});\n   797→```\n   798→\n   799→#### 5.3 Integration Tests\n   800→\n   801→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/RbacIntegrationTest.java`\n   802→\n   803→```java\n   804→@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)\n   805→class RbacIntegrationTest {\n   806→\n   807→    @Test\n   808→    void endToEndRoleChangeFlow() {\n   809→        // 1. User with viewer role tries POST -> 403\n   810→        // 2. Admin assigns write role\n   811→        // 3. User receives SSE notification\n   812→        // 4. User retries POST -> 200\n   813→        // 5. Audit log contains both DENIED and ALLOWED entries\n   814→    }\n   815→}\n   816→```\n   817→\n   818→#### 5.4 Performance Tests\n   819→\n   820→```java\n   821→@Test\n   822→void rbacLatencyP95Under10ms() {\n   823→    // Run 1000 requests\n   824→    // Measure RBAC check time\n   825→    // Assert P95 < 10ms\n   826→}\n   827→```\n   828→\n   829→---\n   830→\n   831→## Files to Create/Modify\n   832→\n   833→### New Files (Backend)\n   834→\n   835→| Path | Purpose |\n   836→|------|---------|\n   837→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Role enum |\n   838→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Identity VO |\n   839→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Permission enum |\n   840→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Decision record |\n   841→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java` | Main RBAC filter |\n   842→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java` | Role resolution with cache |\n   843→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java` | Audit logging |\n   844→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java` | SSE event management |\n   845→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java` | Role assignment ops |\n   846→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java` | Profile service client |\n   847→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java` | Profile DTO |\n   848→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java` | Audit entity |\n   849→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java` | Audit repository |\n   850→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java` | Config class |\n   851→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java` | Properties record |\n   852→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/RbacPathMatcher.java` | Path matching |\n   853→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java` | SSE endpoint |\n   854→| `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` | Audit table migration |\n   855→\n   856→### Modified Files (Backend)\n   857→\n   858→| Path | Changes |\n   859→|------|---------|\n   860→| `backend-mcp/build.gradle` | Add Caffeine cache (if not present) |\n   861→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java` | Add rbac package to scan |\n   862→\n   863→### New Files (Frontend)\n   864→\n   865→| Path | Purpose |\n   866→|------|---------|\n   867→| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` | Role guard hook with SSE |\n   868→| `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` | Role guard component |\n   869→| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` | Hook tests |\n   870→\n   871→### Modified Files (Frontend)\n   872→\n   873→| Path | Changes |\n   874→|------|---------|\n   875→| `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` | Add SSE subscription, roleVersion |\n   876→| `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` | Use useRoleGuard hook |\n   877→| `frontend/src/App.tsx` | Add RoleGuard for admin nav |\n   878→\n   879→---\n   880→\n   881→## Configuration\n   882→\n   883→### application-rbac.yaml\n   884→\n   885→```yaml\n   886→rbac:\n   887→  cache:\n   888→    ttl-minutes: 5\n   889→  protected-paths:\n   890→    - path: \"/api/notes/**\"\n   891→      methods: [\"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"]\n   892→      required-roles: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n   893→    - path: \"/api/admin/**\"\n   894→      methods: [\"*\"]\n   895→      required-roles: [\"admin\"]\n   896→  public-paths:\n   897→    - \"/actuator/health\"\n   898→    - \"/api/public/**\"\n   899→    - \"/api/profiles/role-events\"\n   900→\n   901→profile:\n   902→  service:\n   903→    url: ${PROFILE_SERVICE_URL:http://localhost:8081}\n   904→```\n   905→\n   906→---\n   907→\n   908→## Rollout Plan\n   909→\n   910→### Phase 1: Deploy Backend (Day 13)\n   911→1. Run database migration\n   912→2. Deploy RBAC filter in \"audit-only\" mode (log but don't block)\n   913→3. Monitor audit logs for 24 hours\n   914→\n   915→### Phase 2: Enable Enforcement (Day 14)\n   916→1. Switch RBAC filter to enforcement mode\n   917→2. Monitor 403 rates and latency\n   918→3. Verify cache hit rates\n   919→\n   920→### Phase 3: Frontend Deploy (Day 15)\n   921→1. Deploy updated frontend with SSE subscription\n   922→2. Monitor WebSocket connection rates\n   923→3. Verify role sync within 5 seconds\n   924→\n   925→### Rollback Plan\n   926→- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false)\n   927→- Quick disable via config change\n   928→- Audit logs preserved for analysis\n   929→\n   930→---\n   931→\n   932→## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n   933→\n   934→- [ ] AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for users without required roles\n   935→- [ ] AC-2: All role operations (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED) logged to rbac_audit_log\n   936→- [ ] AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of backend change\n   937→- [ ] AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms under 1000 RPS load\n   938→- [ ] AC-5: Zero breaking changes to existing public APIs\n   939→\n   940→---\n   941→\n   942→## AIDD:METRICS\n   943→\n   944→| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n   945→|--------|--------|-------------|\n   946→| RBAC latency P95 | ≤ 10ms | Micrometer timer on filter |\n   947→| Cache hit rate | ≥ 90% | Caffeine cache stats |\n   948→| Role sync delay | ≤ 5s | Frontend timestamp diff |\n   949→| Audit log coverage | 100% | Count vs request volume |\n   950→| 403 error rate | < 1% | HTTP status metrics |\n   951→\n   952→---\n   953→\n   954→## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n   955→\n   956→None — all questions resolved via research findings.\n   957→\n   958→---\n   959→\n   960→## AIDD:READ_LOG\n   961→\n   962→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n   963→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n   964→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n   965→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n   966→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts`\n   967→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` (excerpt)\n   968→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n   969→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java`\n   970→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/persistence/NoteEntity.java`\n   971→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/notes/db.changelog-master.yaml`\n   972→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/build.gradle`\n   973→\n   974→---\n   975→\n   976→## AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG\n   977→\n   978→- Created plan document with 5 phases\n   979→- Defined 19 new backend files\n   980→- Defined 3 new frontend files\n   981→- Specified 4 modified files\n   982→- Created database migration schema\n   983→- Documented SSE extension approach (vs WebSocket)\n   984→- Documented custom WebFlux filter approach (vs Spring Security)\n   985→\n   986→---\n   987→\n   988→## AIDD:VALIDATION_FEEDBACK\n   989→\n   990→**Validation Status:** WARN (executable after addressing WARN items)\n   991→**Validation Report:** `aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`\n   992→\n   993→### Validation Findings Addressed\n   994→\n   995→| Finding | Status | Resolution |\n   996→|---------|--------|------------|\n   997→| Component scan configuration | Documented | Add RbacConfig to all profile configs |\n   998→| Profile service integration | Documented | Define contract or implement local role storage |\n   999→| RbacPathMatcher implementation | Documented | Complete in Phase 1.6 |\n  1000→| Feature flags for rollout | Recommended | Add to application-rbac.yaml |\n  1001→\n  1002→### Critical Items for Implementation\n  1003→\n  1004→1. **R-008 (High Risk)**: Verify profile service API exists or implement `rbac_profile_roles` table\n  1005→2. **R-007 (Medium Risk)**: Add RBAC configuration to `McpApplication.java` profile imports\n  1006→3. **Path Matcher**: Complete `RbacPathMatcher` implementation with explicit path rules\n  1007→\n  1008→---\n  1009→\n  1010→**Status:** READY for implementation (with validation WARN items noted)\n  1011→**Next Action:** Create tasklist and assign to implementer subagent\n  1012→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"289151de-a4db-4942-a0c0-3b3144dac800","uuid":"76a4056f-0a54-46b5-9371-cbc396ff8e4a","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md","content":"# Implementation Plan — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n**Status:** READY\n**Ticket:** TST-001\n**Updated:** 2026-03-18\n**Research Status:** warn (see research findings for PRD overrides)\n\n---\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThis plan implements live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and frontend role synchronization. Based on research findings, we adapt the PRD assumptions to the actual codebase:\n\n| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Adaptation |\n|----------------|------------------|------------|\n| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom WebFlux filter with header parsing |\n| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend Zustand store with SSE listener |\n| WebSocket push | SSE already exists for flows | Extend SSE for role notifications |\n| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters (no Spring Security) |\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:DECISIONS\n\n### Architecture Decisions\n\n1. **No Spring Security** — Adding spring-boot-starter-security introduces significant complexity and potential conflicts with existing WebFlux setup. Instead, implement custom `WebFilter` for RBAC.\n\n2. **Extend SSE instead of WebSocket** — SSE infrastructure already exists (`subscribeToFlowEvents` in apiClient.ts). Adding WebSocket requires new dependencies and infrastructure. SSE is sufficient for unidirectional server-to-client role updates.\n\n3. **Role Caching with Caffeine** — Backend uses Caffeine cache (already in classpath). Cache profile roles with 5-minute TTL to meet P95 ≤ 10ms latency requirement.\n\n4. **Audit Log as Separate Table** — Follow existing pattern (note_entry table) with PostgreSQL JSONB for flexible metadata.\n\n5. **Header-Based Identity** — Use `X-Profile-Key` (format: `namespace:reference`) and `X-Profile-Auth` headers for identity extraction.\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n\n- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must return 403 for unauthorized requests\n- Audit log must capture: timestamp, actor profile key, action (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED), target resource, result\n- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of backend role change\n- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n- Zero breaking changes to existing API contracts\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:RISKS\n\n| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|------------|\n| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Circuit breaker; fail-closed; cache roles |\n| R-002 | Cache stale roles after assignment | Medium | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change; TTL 5min |\n| R-003 | SSE connection memory leak | Low | Medium | Proper cleanup on disconnect; subscriber limits |\n| R-004 | Audit log write failures | Low | Medium | Async logging; error queue; never block request |\n| R-005 | RBAC filter performance degradation | Low | High | Caffeine cache; async audit; P95 target 10ms |\n| R-006 | Breaking change to existing APIs | Low | High | Feature flags; audit-only mode first; rollback |\n| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High | Add to all profile configs; verify on startup |\n| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High | Define contract; implement fallback to local DB |\n\n### Validation-Derived Risks (from TST-001-validation.md)\n\n**R-007: Component Scan Configuration**\nThe application uses profile-based component scanning. The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.\n- **Mitigation**: Create `RbacConfig.java` with `@Profile(\"!test\")` active in all non-test profiles\n\n**R-008: Profile Service Integration**\nThe plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles was found in research.\n- **Mitigation**: Define profile service contract or implement local role storage via `rbac_profile_roles` table\n\n---\n\n## Milestones & Iterations\n\n### Phase 1: Backend Foundation (Days 1-3)\n**Goal:** Core RBAC filter and audit infrastructure\n\n#### 1.1 Database Migration\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n# Create audit_log table\n- changeSet:\n    id: rbac-0001-audit-log\n    author: ai-advent\n    context: rbac\n    changes:\n      - createTable:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: id\n                type: UUID\n                defaultValueComputed: gen_random_uuid()\n                constraints:\n                  primaryKey: true\n            - column:\n                name: timestamp\n                type: TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE\n                defaultValueComputed: now()\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: actor_namespace\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: actor_reference\n                type: VARCHAR(128)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: action\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: target_resource\n                type: VARCHAR(256)\n            - column:\n                name: target_profile_namespace\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n            - column:\n                name: target_profile_reference\n                type: VARCHAR(128)\n            - column:\n                name: result\n                type: VARCHAR(16)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: http_method\n                type: VARCHAR(8)\n            - column:\n                name: http_path\n                type: VARCHAR(512)\n            - column:\n                name: metadata\n                type: JSONB\n      - createIndex:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_timestamp\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: timestamp\n      - createIndex:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_actor\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: actor_namespace\n            - column:\n                name: actor_reference\n```\n\n#### 1.2 RBAC Core Domain\n**Files to create:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Enum: ADMIN, USER, VIEWER, etc. |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Value object: namespace + reference |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Enum: READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Record: allowed (boolean), reason (string) |\n\n#### 1.3 RBAC Filter (WebFlux)\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java`\n\n```java\n@Component\n@Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100) // After logging, before business logic\npublic class RbacWebFilter implements WebFilter {\n\n    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n    private final RbacPathMatcher pathMatcher;\n\n    @Override\n    public Mono<Void> filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {\n        HttpMethod method = exchange.getRequest().getMethod();\n        String path = exchange.getRequest().getPath().value();\n\n        // Skip non-mutation methods\n        if (!isMutationMethod(method)) {\n            return chain.filter(exchange);\n        }\n\n        // Skip excluded paths (health, public APIs)\n        if (pathMatcher.isPublicPath(path)) {\n            return chain.filter(exchange);\n        }\n\n        // Extract identity from headers\n        ProfileIdentity identity = extractIdentity(exchange.getRequest());\n        if (identity == null) {\n            return auditAndDeny(exchange, null, path, method, \"Missing identity headers\");\n        }\n\n        // Check required roles for path\n        Set<Role> requiredRoles = pathMatcher.getRequiredRoles(path, method);\n\n        return roleService.hasAnyRole(identity, requiredRoles)\n            .flatMap(hasRole -> {\n                if (hasRole) {\n                    auditService.logAccess(identity, path, method, \"ALLOWED\");\n                    return chain.filter(exchange);\n                } else {\n                    return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"Insufficient permissions\");\n                }\n            })\n            .onErrorResume(e -> {\n                log.error(\"RBAC check failed\", e);\n                return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"RBAC error: \" + e.getMessage());\n            });\n    }\n\n    private Mono<Void> auditAndDeny(ServerWebExchange exchange, ProfileIdentity identity,\n                                     String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n        auditService.logDenied(identity, path, method, reason);\n        exchange.getResponse().setStatusCode(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);\n        exchange.getResponse().getHeaders().setContentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);\n        String body = String.format(\"{\\\"error\\\":\\\"Forbidden\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"%s\\\"}\", reason);\n        DataBuffer buffer = exchange.getResponse().bufferFactory().wrap(body.getBytes());\n        return exchange.getResponse().writeWith(Mono.just(buffer));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.4 Profile Role Service with Caching\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class ProfileRoleService {\n\n    private final LoadingCache<ProfileIdentity, Set<Role>> roleCache;\n    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n\n    public ProfileRoleService(ProfileClient profileClient,\n                              @Value(\"${rbac.cache.ttl-minutes:5}\") int cacheTtlMinutes) {\n        this.profileClient = profileClient;\n        this.roleCache = Caffeine.newBuilder()\n            .expireAfterWrite(cacheTtlMinutes, TimeUnit.MINUTES)\n            .maximumSize(10_000)\n            .recordStats()\n            .build(this::loadRoles);\n    }\n\n    private Set<Role> loadRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        return profileClient.fetchRoles(identity);\n    }\n\n    public Mono<Boolean> hasAnyRole(ProfileIdentity identity, Set<Role> requiredRoles) {\n        if (requiredRoles.isEmpty()) {\n            return Mono.just(true);\n        }\n        return Mono.fromCallable(() -> roleCache.get(identity))\n            .subscribeOn(Schedulers.boundedElastic())\n            .map(userRoles -> userRoles.stream().anyMatch(requiredRoles::contains));\n    }\n\n    public void invalidateCache(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        roleCache.invalidate(identity);\n    }\n\n    public CacheStats getCacheStats() {\n        return roleCache.stats();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.5 Audit Log Service\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class AuditLogService {\n\n    private final AuditLogRepository repository;\n    private final ExecutorService asyncExecutor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);\n\n    public void logAccess(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String result) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n            entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n            entry.setAction(\"ACCESS\");\n            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n            entry.setResult(result);\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    public void logDenied(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            if (identity != null) {\n                entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n                entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n            }\n            entry.setAction(\"DENIED\");\n            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n            entry.setResult(\"DENIED\");\n            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"reason\", reason));\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    public void logRoleChange(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target,\n                              String action, Set<Role> roles) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            entry.setActorNamespace(actor.namespace());\n            entry.setActorReference(actor.reference());\n            entry.setAction(action); // GRANT or REVOKE\n            entry.setTargetProfileNamespace(target.namespace());\n            entry.setTargetProfileReference(target.reference());\n            entry.setResult(\"SUCCESS\");\n            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"roles\", roles));\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    private void asyncLog(Runnable task) {\n        asyncExecutor.submit(() -> {\n            try {\n                task.run();\n            } catch (Exception e) {\n                log.error(\"Failed to write audit log\", e);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.6 Audit Log Entity & Repository\n**Files:**\n- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java`\n- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java`\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Profile Service Integration (Days 4-5)\n**Goal:** Connect to existing profile service for role resolution\n\n#### 2.1 Profile Client\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java`\n\n```java\n@Component\npublic class ProfileClient {\n\n    private final WebClient webClient;\n    private final String profileServiceUrl;\n\n    public ProfileClient(@Value(\"${profile.service.url}\") String profileServiceUrl,\n                         WebClient.Builder webClientBuilder) {\n        this.profileServiceUrl = profileServiceUrl;\n        this.webClient = webClientBuilder.baseUrl(profileServiceUrl).build();\n    }\n\n    public Set<Role> fetchRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        try {\n            ProfileResponse response = webClient.get()\n                .uri(\"/api/profiles/{namespace}/{reference}\", identity.namespace(), identity.reference())\n                .retrieve()\n                .bodyToMono(ProfileResponse.class)\n                .timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(2))\n                .block();\n\n            return response != null && response.roles() != null\n                ? response.roles().stream().map(Role::valueOf).collect(Collectors.toSet())\n                : Set.of();\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            log.error(\"Failed to fetch roles for {}\", identity, e);\n            // Fail-closed: return empty set (deny access)\n            return Set.of();\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 2.2 Profile Response DTO\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java`\n\n```java\npublic record ProfileResponse(\n    String profileId,\n    String namespace,\n    String reference,\n    List<String> roles,\n    Instant updatedAt\n) {}\n```\n\n#### 2.3 RBAC Configuration\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java`\n\n```java\n@Configuration\n@EnableConfigurationProperties(RbacProperties.class)\npublic class RbacConfiguration {\n\n    @Bean\n    public RbacPathMatcher rbacPathMatcher(RbacProperties properties) {\n        return new RbacPathMatcher(properties);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java`\n\n```java\n@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = \"rbac\")\npublic record RbacProperties(\n    List<PathRule> protectedPaths,\n    List<String> publicPaths,\n    int cacheTtlMinutes\n) {\n    public record PathRule(\n        String path,\n        Set<String> methods,\n        Set<String> requiredRoles\n    ) {}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Frontend Role Sync (Days 6-8)\n**Goal:** Real-time role synchronization via SSE\n\n#### 3.1 Extend Profile Store with SSE\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n\n```typescript\n// Add to ProfileStoreState\ntype ProfileStoreState = {\n  // ... existing fields\n  roleVersion: number; // Incremented on role change\n  lastRoleSync: string | null;\n  subscribeToRoleChanges: () => () => void;\n};\n\n// Add to store implementation\nexport const useProfileStore = create<ProfileStoreState>()(\n  persist(\n    (set, get) => ({\n      // ... existing initial state\n      roleVersion: 0,\n      lastRoleSync: null,\n\n      subscribeToRoleChanges: () => {\n        const { namespace, reference, channel, devToken } = getActiveProfileSelection();\n        if (!namespace || !reference) return () => {};\n\n        const params = new URLSearchParams();\n        params.set('namespace', namespace);\n        params.set('reference', reference);\n        if (channel) params.set('channel', channel);\n        if (devToken) params.set('token', devToken);\n\n        const eventSource = new EventSource(\n          `${API_BASE_URL}/api/profiles/role-events?${params.toString()}`\n        );\n\n        eventSource.addEventListener('role-change', (event) => {\n          const data = JSON.parse(event.data);\n          set((state) => ({\n            profile: state.profile ? {\n              ...state.profile,\n              roles: data.roles,\n              updatedAt: data.timestamp,\n            } : null,\n            roleVersion: state.roleVersion + 1,\n            lastRoleSync: new Date().toISOString(),\n          }));\n        });\n\n        eventSource.onerror = () => {\n          // Auto-reconnect handled by browser, but we log it\n          console.warn('Role events connection error, will retry...');\n        };\n\n        return () => eventSource.close();\n      },\n    }),\n    // ... existing persist config\n  ),\n);\n```\n\n#### 3.2 Create useRoleGuard Hook\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport { useEffect, useMemo } from 'react';\nimport { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n\nexport function useRoleGuard(requiredRole?: string) {\n  const roles = useProfileStore((state) => state.profile?.roles ?? []);\n  const roleVersion = useProfileStore((state) => state.roleVersion);\n\n  // Subscribe to role changes on mount\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const unsubscribe = useProfileStore.getState().subscribeToRoleChanges();\n    return unsubscribe;\n  }, []);\n\n  const hasRole = useMemo(() => {\n    if (!requiredRole) return true;\n    return roles.some((role) => role === requiredRole);\n  }, [roles, requiredRole, roleVersion]);\n\n  const hasAnyRole = useMemo(() => {\n    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roles.some((role) => roleCodes.includes(role));\n  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n\n  const hasAllRoles = useMemo(() => {\n    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roleCodes.every((role) => roles.includes(role));\n  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n\n  return {\n    roles,\n    hasRole,\n    hasAnyRole,\n    hasAllRoles,\n    isAdmin: roles.includes('admin'),\n    roleVersion,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.3 Update AdminRoles Page\n**File:** `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n\nReplace inline role check with hook:\n\n```typescript\n// Replace lines 34-36:\nconst { isAdmin } = useRoleGuard('admin');\n\n// Replace hasAdminRole references with isAdmin\n```\n\n#### 3.4 Create RoleGuard Component\n**File:** `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport React from 'react';\nimport { useRoleGuard } from '../lib/useRoleGuard';\n\ninterface RoleGuardProps {\n  requiredRole: string;\n  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport const RoleGuard: React.FC<RoleGuardProps> = ({\n  requiredRole,\n  fallback = null,\n  children,\n}) => {\n  const { hasRole } = useRoleGuard(requiredRole);\n  return hasRole ? <>{children}</> : <>{fallback}</>;\n};\n\ninterface AdminGuardProps {\n  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport const AdminGuard: React.FC<AdminGuardProps> = ({ fallback, children }) => (\n  <RoleGuard requiredRole=\"admin\" fallback={fallback}>\n    {children}\n  </RoleGuard>\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: SSE Role Events Endpoint (Days 9-10)\n**Goal:** Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications\n\n#### 4.1 Role Event Service\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class RoleEventService {\n\n    private final Map<ProfileIdentity, Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent>> subscribers = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();\n\n    public Flux<RoleChangeEvent> subscribe(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = Sinks.many().multicast().onBackpressureBuffer();\n        subscribers.put(identity, sink);\n\n        return sink.asFlux()\n            .doOnCancel(() -> subscribers.remove(identity))\n            .doOnTerminate(() -> subscribers.remove(identity));\n    }\n\n    public void notifyRoleChange(ProfileIdentity identity, List<String> roles) {\n        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = subscribers.get(identity);\n        if (sink != null) {\n            sink.tryEmitNext(new RoleChangeEvent(roles, Instant.now()));\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void broadcastRoleChange(ProfileIdentity target, List<String> roles) {\n        notifyRoleChange(target, roles);\n    }\n\n    public record RoleChangeEvent(List<String> roles, Instant timestamp) {}\n}\n```\n\n#### 4.2 SSE Controller\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java`\n\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/profiles\")\npublic class RoleEventsController {\n\n    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n\n    @GetMapping(value = \"/role-events\", produces = MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)\n    public Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> roleEvents(\n            @RequestParam String namespace,\n            @RequestParam String reference,\n            @RequestParam(required = false) String channel,\n            @RequestParam(required = false) String token) {\n\n        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(namespace, reference);\n\n        return eventService.subscribe(identity)\n            .map(event -> ServerSentEvent.builder(event)\n                .event(\"role-change\")\n                .id(UUID.randomUUID().toString())\n                .build())\n            .mergeWith(heartbeatFlux());\n    }\n\n    private Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> heartbeatFlux() {\n        return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(30))\n            .map(i -> ServerSentEvent.<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>builder()\n                .comment(\"heartbeat\")\n                .build());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 4.3 Integrate with Admin Role Operations\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class RoleAssignmentService {\n\n    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n\n    public Mono<Void> assignRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n        return profileClient.assignRole(target, role)\n            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n                // Invalidate cache\n                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n                // Notify user\n                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n                // Audit\n                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"GRANT\", Set.of(role));\n            });\n    }\n\n    public Mono<Void> revokeRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n        return profileClient.revokeRole(target, role)\n            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"REVOKE\", Set.of(role));\n            });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Testing & Validation (Days 11-12)\n**Goal:** Comprehensive test coverage\n\n#### 5.1 Backend Tests\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilterTest.java`\n\n```java\n@WebFluxTest(RbacWebFilter.class)\nclass RbacWebFilterTest {\n\n    @MockBean\n    private ProfileRoleService roleService;\n\n    @MockBean\n    private AuditLogService auditService;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private WebTestClient webClient;\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldAllowGetRequestWithoutRole() {\n        webClient.get().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isOk();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldDenyPostWithoutRole() {\n        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(false));\n\n        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isForbidden();\n\n        verify(auditService).logDenied(any(), eq(\"/api/test\"), eq(HttpMethod.POST), any());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldAllowPostWithAdminRole() {\n        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(true));\n\n        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:admin\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isOk();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleServiceTest.java`\n\n```java\nclass ProfileRoleServiceTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldCacheRoles() {\n        // First call hits profile service\n        // Second call uses cache\n        // Verify cache stats\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldFailClosedOnError() {\n        // When profile service unavailable\n        // Return empty roles (deny access)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 5.2 Frontend Tests\n\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport { renderHook, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { useRoleGuard } from './useRoleGuard';\nimport { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n\ndescribe('useRoleGuard', () => {\n  it('should update when roles change', async () => {\n    const { result } = renderHook(() => useRoleGuard('admin'));\n\n    expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(false);\n\n    // Simulate role change event\n    useProfileStore.setState({\n      profile: { roles: ['admin'] } as UserProfileDocument,\n      roleVersion: 1,\n    });\n\n    await waitFor(() => {\n      expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(true);\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n#### 5.3 Integration Tests\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/RbacIntegrationTest.java`\n\n```java\n@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)\nclass RbacIntegrationTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void endToEndRoleChangeFlow() {\n        // 1. User with viewer role tries POST -> 403\n        // 2. Admin assigns write role\n        // 3. User receives SSE notification\n        // 4. User retries POST -> 200\n        // 5. Audit log contains both DENIED and ALLOWED entries\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 5.4 Performance Tests\n\n```java\n@Test\nvoid rbacLatencyP95Under10ms() {\n    // Run 1000 requests\n    // Measure RBAC check time\n    // Assert P95 < 10ms\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n### New Files (Backend)\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Role enum |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Identity VO |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Permission enum |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Decision record |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java` | Main RBAC filter |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java` | Role resolution with cache |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java` | Audit logging |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java` | SSE event management |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java` | Role assignment ops |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java` | Profile service client |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java` | Profile DTO |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java` | Audit entity |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java` | Audit repository |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java` | Config class |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java` | Properties record |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/RbacPathMatcher.java` | Path matching |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java` | SSE endpoint |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` | Audit table migration |\n\n### Modified Files (Backend)\n\n| Path | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/build.gradle` | Add Caffeine cache (if not present) |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java` | Add rbac package to scan |\n\n### New Files (Frontend)\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` | Role guard hook with SSE |\n| `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` | Role guard component |\n| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` | Hook tests |\n\n### Modified Files (Frontend)\n\n| Path | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` | Add SSE subscription, roleVersion |\n| `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` | Use useRoleGuard hook |\n| `frontend/src/App.tsx` | Add RoleGuard for admin nav |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### application-rbac.yaml\n\n```yaml\nrbac:\n  cache:\n    ttl-minutes: 5\n  protected-paths:\n    - path: \"/api/notes/**\"\n      methods: [\"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"]\n      required-roles: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n    - path: \"/api/admin/**\"\n      methods: [\"*\"]\n      required-roles: [\"admin\"]\n  public-paths:\n    - \"/actuator/health\"\n    - \"/api/public/**\"\n    - \"/api/profiles/role-events\"\n\nprofile:\n  service:\n    url: ${PROFILE_SERVICE_URL:http://localhost:8081}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Rollout Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Deploy Backend (Day 13)\n1. Run database migration\n2. Deploy RBAC filter in \"audit-only\" mode (log but don't block)\n3. Monitor audit logs for 24 hours\n\n### Phase 2: Enable Enforcement (Day 14)\n1. Switch RBAC filter to enforcement mode\n2. Monitor 403 rates and latency\n3. Verify cache hit rates\n\n### Phase 3: Frontend Deploy (Day 15)\n1. Deploy updated frontend with SSE subscription\n2. Monitor WebSocket connection rates\n3. Verify role sync within 5 seconds\n\n### Rollback Plan\n- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false)\n- Quick disable via config change\n- Audit logs preserved for analysis\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n\n- [ ] AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for users without required roles\n- [ ] AC-2: All role operations (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED) logged to rbac_audit_log\n- [ ] AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of backend change\n- [ ] AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms under 1000 RPS load\n- [ ] AC-5: Zero breaking changes to existing public APIs\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:METRICS\n\n| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| RBAC latency P95 | ≤ 10ms | Micrometer timer on filter |\n| Cache hit rate | ≥ 90% | Caffeine cache stats |\n| Role sync delay | ≤ 5s | Frontend timestamp diff |\n| Audit log coverage | 100% | Count vs request volume |\n| 403 error rate | < 1% | HTTP status metrics |\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n\nNone — all questions resolved via research findings.\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:READ_LOG\n\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` (excerpt)\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/persistence/NoteEntity.java`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/notes/db.changelog-master.yaml`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/build.gradle`\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG\n\n- Created plan document with 5 phases\n- Defined 19 new backend files\n- Defined 3 new frontend files\n- Specified 4 modified files\n- Created database migration schema\n- Documented SSE extension approach (vs WebSocket)\n- Documented custom WebFlux filter approach (vs Spring Security)\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:VALIDATION_FEEDBACK\n\n**Validation Status:** WARN (executable after addressing WARN items)\n**Validation Report:** `aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`\n\n### Validation Findings Addressed\n\n| Finding | Status | Resolution |\n|---------|--------|------------|\n| Component scan configuration | Documented | Add RbacConfig to all profile configs |\n| Profile service integration | Documented | Define contract or implement local role storage |\n| RbacPathMatcher implementation | Documented | Complete in Phase 1.6 |\n| Feature flags for rollout | Recommended | Add to application-rbac.yaml |\n\n### Critical Items for Implementation\n\n1. **R-008 (High Risk)**: Verify profile service API exists or implement `rbac_profile_roles` table\n2. **R-007 (Medium Risk)**: Add RBAC configuration to `McpApplication.java` profile imports\n3. **Path Matcher**: Complete `RbacPathMatcher` implementation with explicit path rules\n\n---\n\n**Status:** READY for implementation (with validation WARN items noted)\n**Next Action:** Create tasklist and assign to implementer subagent\n","numLines":1012,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1012}}}
