{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_01LFkz1f3RoihRCdJ7i1rnEd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.domain;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n     4→import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n     5→\n     6→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     7→\n     8→class ProfileIdentityTest {\n     9→\n    10→    @Test\n    11→    void shouldCreateProfileIdentityWithValidValues() {\n    12→        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(\"github\", \"user123\");\n    13→\n    14→        assertThat(identity.namespace()).isEqualTo(\"github\");\n    15→        assertThat(identity.reference()).isEqualTo(\"user123\");\n    16→    }\n    17→\n    18→    @Test\n    19→    void shouldThrowExceptionWhenNamespaceIsNull() {\n    20→        assertThatThrownBy(() -> new ProfileIdentity(null, \"user123\"))\n    21→                .isInstanceOf(NullPointerException.class)\n    22→                .hasMessageContaining(\"namespace\");\n    23→    }\n    24→\n    25→    @Test\n    26→    void shouldThrowExceptionWhenReferenceIsNull() {\n    27→        assertThatThrownBy(() -> new ProfileIdentity(\"github\", null))\n    28→                .isInstanceOf(NullPointerException.class)\n    29→                .hasMessageContaining(\"reference\");\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    @Test\n    33→    void shouldThrowExceptionWhenNamespaceIsBlank() {\n    34→        assertThatThrownBy(() -> new ProfileIdentity(\"\", \"user123\"))\n    35→                .isInstanceOf(IllegalArgumentException.class)\n    36→                .hasMessageContaining(\"namespace\");\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    @Test\n    40→    void shouldThrowExceptionWhenReferenceIsBlank() {\n    41→        assertThatThrownBy(() -> new ProfileIdentity(\"github\", \"\"))\n    42→                .isInstanceOf(IllegalArgumentException.class)\n    43→                .hasMessageContaining(\"reference\");\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    @Test\n    47→    void shouldThrowExceptionWhenNamespaceIsWhitespace() {\n    48→        assertThatThrownBy(() -> new ProfileIdentity(\"   \", \"user123\"))\n    49→                .isInstanceOf(IllegalArgumentException.class)\n    50→                .hasMessageContaining(\"namespace\");\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    @Test\n    54→    void shouldThrowExceptionWhenReferenceIsWhitespace() {\n    55→        assertThatThrownBy(() -> new ProfileIdentity(\"github\", \"   \"))\n    56→                .isInstanceOf(IllegalArgumentException.class)\n    57→                .hasMessageContaining(\"reference\");\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    @Test\n    61→    void shouldFormatToStringAsNamespaceColonReference() {\n    62→        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(\"github\", \"user123\");\n    63→\n    64→        assertThat(identity.toString()).isEqualTo(\"github:user123\");\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    @Test\n    68→    void shouldHandleDifferentNamespacesInToString() {\n    69→        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(\"local\", \"admin\");\n    70→\n    71→        assertThat(identity.toString()).isEqualTo(\"local:admin\");\n    72→    }\n    73→}\n    74→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_jnoL07xIqIHBJzjGJA8vP9R2","session_id":"289151de-a4db-4942-a0c0-3b3144dac800","uuid":"3d59a69a-5d17-492d-aa33-fc0b4a9a97c6"}
